   96  /// A NamespaceResult represents the result of resolving an import in
   97  /// a particular namespace. The result is either definitely-resolved,
   98  /// definitely- unresolved, or unknown.
   99  pub enum NamespaceResult {
  100      /// Means that resolve hasn't gathered enough information yet to determine
  101      /// whether the name is bound in this namespace. (That is, it hasn't
  102      /// resolved all `use` directives yet.)
  103      UnknownResult,
  104      /// Means that resolve has determined that the name is definitely
  105      /// not bound in the namespace.
  106      UnboundResult,
  107      /// Means that resolve has determined that the name is bound in the Module
  108      /// argument, and specified by the NameBindings argument.
  109      BoundResult(@mut Module, @mut NameBindings)
  110  }
  111  
  112  impl NamespaceResult {
  113      pub fn is_unknown(&self) -> bool {
  114          match *self {
  115              UnknownResult => true,
  116              _ => false
  117          }
  118      }
  119  }

  124      ImportNameDefinition(Def)   //< The name identifies an import.
  125  }

  138  struct ResolveVisitor {
  139      resolver: @mut Resolver,
  140  }
  141  
  142  impl Visitor<()> for ResolveVisitor {
  143      fn visit_item(&mut self, item:@item, _:()) {
  144          self.resolver.resolve_item(item, self);
  145      }
  146      fn visit_arm(&mut self, arm:&Arm, _:()) {
  147          self.resolver.resolve_arm(arm, self);
  148      }
  149      fn visit_block(&mut self, block:&Block, _:()) {
  150          self.resolver.resolve_block(block, self);
  151      }
  152      fn visit_expr(&mut self, expr:@Expr, _:()) {
  153          self.resolver.resolve_expr(expr, self);
  154      }
  155      fn visit_local(&mut self, local:@Local, _:()) {
  156          self.resolver.resolve_local(local, self);
  157      }
  158      fn visit_ty(&mut self, ty:&Ty, _:()) {
  159          self.resolver.resolve_type(ty, self);
  160      }
  161  }

  175  pub enum ResolveResult<T> {
  176      Failed,         // Failed to resolve the name.
  177      Indeterminate,  // Couldn't determine due to unresolved globs.
  178      Success(T)      // Successfully resolved the import.
  179  }
  180  
  181  impl<T> ResolveResult<T> {
  182      pub fn failed(&self) -> bool {
  183          match *self { Failed => true, _ => false }
  184      }
  185      pub fn indeterminate(&self) -> bool {
  186          match *self { Indeterminate => true, _ => false }
  187      }
  188  }
  189  
  190  pub enum TypeParameters<'self> {
  191      NoTypeParameters,                   //< No type parameters.
  192      HasTypeParameters(&'self Generics,  //< Type parameters.
  193                        NodeId,          //< ID of the enclosing item
  194  
  195                        // The index to start numbering the type parameters at.
  196                        // This is zero if this is the outermost set of type
  197                        // parameters, or equal to the number of outer type
  198                        // parameters. For example, if we have:
  199                        //
  200                        //   impl I<T> {
  201                        //     fn method<U>() { ... }
  202                        //   }
  203                        //
  204                        // The index at the method site will be 1, because the
  205                        // outer T had index 0.
  206                        uint,
  207  
  208                        // The kind of the rib used for type parameters.
  209                        RibKind)
  210  }
  211  
  212  // The rib kind controls the translation of argument or local definitions
  213  // (`def_arg` or `def_local`) to upvars (`def_upvar`).
  214  
  215  pub enum RibKind {
  216      // No translation needs to be applied.
  217      NormalRibKind,
  218  
  219      // We passed through a function scope at the given node ID. Translate
  220      // upvars as appropriate.
  221      FunctionRibKind(NodeId /* func id */, NodeId /* body id */),
  222  
  223      // We passed through an impl or trait and are now in one of its
  224      // methods. Allow references to ty params that impl or trait
  225      // binds. Disallow any other upvars (including other ty params that are
  226      // upvars).
  227                // parent;   method itself
  228      MethodRibKind(NodeId, MethodSort),
  229  
  230      // We passed through a function *item* scope. Disallow upvars.
  231      OpaqueFunctionRibKind,
  232  
  233      // We're in a constant item. Can't refer to dynamic stuff.
  234      ConstantItemRibKind
  235  }
  236  
  237  // Methods can be required or provided. Required methods only occur in traits.
  238  pub enum MethodSort {
  239      Required,
  240      Provided(NodeId)
  241  }

  372  /// An ImportResolution represents a particular `use` directive.
  373  pub struct ImportResolution {
  374      /// The privacy of this `use` directive (whether it's `use` or
  375      /// `pub use`.
  376      privacy: Privacy,
  377  
  378      // The number of outstanding references to this name. When this reaches
  379      // zero, outside modules can count on the targets being correct. Before
  380      // then, all bets are off; future imports could override this name.
  381      outstanding_references: uint,
  382  
  383      /// The value that this `use` directive names, if there is one.
  384      value_target: Option<Target>,
  385      /// The source node of the `use` directive leading to the value target
  386      /// being non-none
  387      value_id: NodeId,
  388  
  389      /// The type that this `use` directive names, if there is one.
  390      type_target: Option<Target>,
  391      /// The source node of the `use` directive leading to the type target
  392      /// being non-none
  393      type_id: NodeId,
  394  }
  395  
  396  impl ImportResolution {
  397      pub fn new(privacy: Privacy,
  398                 id: NodeId) -> ImportResolution {
  399          ImportResolution {
  400              privacy: privacy,
  401              type_id: id,
  402              value_id: id,
  403              outstanding_references: 0,
  404              value_target: None,
  405              type_target: None,
  406          }
  407      }
  408  
  409      pub fn target_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace)
  410                                  -> Option<Target> {
  411          match namespace {
  412              TypeNS      => return self.type_target,
  413              ValueNS     => return self.value_target,
  414          }
  415      }
  416  
  417      fn id(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> NodeId {
  418          match namespace {
  419              TypeNS  => self.type_id,
  420              ValueNS => self.value_id,
  421          }
  422      }
  423  }

  432  /// The type of module this is.

  435      NormalModuleKind,

  441  
  442  /// One node in the tree of modules.
  443  pub struct Module {
  444      parent_link: ParentLink,
  445      def_id: Option<DefId>,
  446      kind: ModuleKind,
  447  
  448      children: @mut HashMap<Name, @mut NameBindings>,
  449      imports: @mut ~[@ImportDirective],
  450  
  451      // The external module children of this node that were declared with
  452      // `extern mod`.
  453      external_module_children: @mut HashMap<Name, @mut Module>,
  454  
  455      // The anonymous children of this node. Anonymous children are pseudo-
  456      // modules that are implicitly created around items contained within
  457      // blocks.
  458      //
  459      // For example, if we have this:
  460      //
  461      //  fn f() {
  462      //      fn g() {
  463      //          ...
  464      //      }
  465      //  }
  466      //
  467      // There will be an anonymous module created around `g` with the ID of the
  468      // entry block for `f`.
  469      anonymous_children: @mut HashMap<NodeId,@mut Module>,
  470  
  471      // The status of resolving each import in this module.
  472      import_resolutions: @mut HashMap<Name, @mut ImportResolution>,
  473  
  474      // The number of unresolved globs that this module exports.
  475      glob_count: uint,
  476  
  477      // The index of the import we're resolving.
  478      resolved_import_count: uint,
  479  
  480      // Whether this module is populated. If not populated, any attempt to
  481      // access the children must be preceded with a
  482      // `populate_module_if_necessary` call.
  483      populated: bool,
  484  }
  485  
  486  impl Module {
  487      pub fn new(parent_link: ParentLink,
  488                  def_id: Option<DefId>,
  489                  kind: ModuleKind,
  490                  external: bool)
  491                  -> Module {
  492          Module {
  493              parent_link: parent_link,
  494              def_id: def_id,
  495              kind: kind,
  496              children: @mut HashMap::new(),
  497              imports: @mut ~[],
  498              external_module_children: @mut HashMap::new(),
  499              anonymous_children: @mut HashMap::new(),
  500              import_resolutions: @mut HashMap::new(),
  501              glob_count: 0,
  502              resolved_import_count: 0,
  503              populated: !external,
  504          }
  505      }
  506  
  507      pub fn all_imports_resolved(&self) -> bool {
  508          let imports = &mut *self.imports;
  509          return imports.len() == self.resolved_import_count;
  510      }
  511  }
  512  
  513  // Records a possibly-private type definition.
  514  pub struct TypeNsDef {
  515      privacy: Privacy,
  516      module_def: Option<@mut Module>,
  517      type_def: Option<Def>,
  518      type_span: Option<Span>
  519  }
  520  
  521  // Records a possibly-private value definition.
  522  pub struct ValueNsDef {
  523      privacy: Privacy,
  524      def: Def,
  525      value_span: Option<Span>,
  526  }
  527  
  528  // Records the definitions (at most one for each namespace) that a name is
  529  // bound to.
  530  pub struct NameBindings {
  531      type_def: Option<TypeNsDef>,    //< Meaning in type namespace.
  532      value_def: Option<ValueNsDef>,  //< Meaning in value namespace.
  533  }
  534  
  535  /// Ways in which a trait can be referenced
  536  enum TraitReferenceType {
  537      TraitImplementation,             // impl SomeTrait for T { ... }
  538      TraitDerivation,                 // trait T : SomeTrait { ... }
  539      TraitBoundingTypeParameter,      // fn f<T:SomeTrait>() { ... }
  540  }
  541  
  542  impl NameBindings {
  543      /// Creates a new module in this set of name bindings.
  544      pub fn define_module(@mut self,
  545                           privacy: Privacy,
  546                           parent_link: ParentLink,
  547                           def_id: Option<DefId>,
  548                           kind: ModuleKind,
  549                           external: bool,
  550                           sp: Span) {
  551          // Merges the module with the existing type def or creates a new one.
  552          let module_ = @mut Module::new(parent_link, def_id, kind, external);
  553          match self.type_def {
  554              None => {
  555                  self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  556                      privacy: privacy,
  557                      module_def: Some(module_),
  558                      type_def: None,
  559                      type_span: Some(sp)
  560                  });
  561              }
  562              Some(type_def) => {
  563                  self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  564                      privacy: privacy,
  565                      module_def: Some(module_),
  566                      type_span: Some(sp),
  567                      type_def: type_def.type_def
  568                  });
  569              }
  570          }
  571      }
  572  
  573      /// Sets the kind of the module, creating a new one if necessary.
  574      pub fn set_module_kind(@mut self,
  575                             privacy: Privacy,
  576                             parent_link: ParentLink,
  577                             def_id: Option<DefId>,
  578                             kind: ModuleKind,
  579                             external: bool,
  580                             _sp: Span) {
  581          match self.type_def {
  582              None => {
  583                  let module = @mut Module::new(parent_link, def_id, kind, external);
  584                  self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  585                      privacy: privacy,
  586                      module_def: Some(module),
  587                      type_def: None,
  588                      type_span: None,
  589                  })
  590              }
  591              Some(type_def) => {
  592                  match type_def.module_def {
  593                      None => {
  594                          let module = @mut Module::new(parent_link,
  595                                                   def_id,
  596                                                   kind,
  597                                                   external);
  598                          self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  599                              privacy: privacy,
  600                              module_def: Some(module),
  601                              type_def: type_def.type_def,
  602                              type_span: None,
  603                          })
  604                      }
  605                      Some(module_def) => module_def.kind = kind,
  606                  }
  607              }
  608          }
  609      }
  610  
  611      /// Records a type definition.
  612      pub fn define_type(@mut self, privacy: Privacy, def: Def, sp: Span) {
  613          // Merges the type with the existing type def or creates a new one.
  614          match self.type_def {
  615              None => {
  616                  self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  617                      privacy: privacy,
  618                      module_def: None,
  619                      type_def: Some(def),
  620                      type_span: Some(sp)
  621                  });
  622              }
  623              Some(type_def) => {
  624                  self.type_def = Some(TypeNsDef {
  625                      privacy: privacy,
  626                      type_def: Some(def),
  627                      type_span: Some(sp),
  628                      module_def: type_def.module_def
  629                  });
  630              }
  631          }
  632      }
  633  
  634      /// Records a value definition.
  635      pub fn define_value(@mut self, privacy: Privacy, def: Def, sp: Span) {
  636          self.value_def = Some(ValueNsDef { privacy: privacy, def: def, value_span: Some(sp) });
  637      }
  638  
  639      /// Returns the module node if applicable.
  640      pub fn get_module_if_available(&self) -> Option<@mut Module> {
  641          match self.type_def {
  642              Some(ref type_def) => (*type_def).module_def,
  643              None => None
  644          }
  645      }
  646  
  647      /**
  648       * Returns the module node. Fails if this node does not have a module
  649       * definition.
  650       */
  651      pub fn get_module(@mut self) -> @mut Module {
  652          match self.get_module_if_available() {
  653              None => {
  654                  fail!("get_module called on a node with no module \
  655                         definition!")
  656              }
  657              Some(module_def) => module_def
  658          }
  659      }
  660  
  661      pub fn defined_in_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> bool {
  662          match namespace {
  663              TypeNS   => return self.type_def.is_some(),
  664              ValueNS  => return self.value_def.is_some()
  665          }
  666      }
  667  
  668      pub fn defined_in_public_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> bool {
  669          match namespace {
  670              TypeNS => match self.type_def {
  671                  Some(def) => def.privacy != Private,
  672                  None => false
  673              },
  674              ValueNS => match self.value_def {
  675                  Some(def) => def.privacy != Private,
  676                  None => false
  677              }
  678          }
  679      }
  680  
  681      pub fn def_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> Option<Def> {
  682          match namespace {
  683              TypeNS => {
  684                  match self.type_def {
  685                      None => None,
  686                      Some(ref type_def) => {
  687                          match (*type_def).type_def {
  688                              Some(type_def) => Some(type_def),
  689                              None => {
  690                                  match type_def.module_def {
  691                                      Some(module) => {
  692                                          match module.def_id {
  693                                              Some(did) => Some(DefMod(did)),
  694                                              None => None,
  695                                          }
  696                                      }
  697                                      None => None,
  698                                  }
  699                              }
  700                          }
  701                      }
  702                  }
  703              }
  704              ValueNS => {
  705                  match self.value_def {
  706                      None => None,
  707                      Some(value_def) => Some(value_def.def)
  708                  }
  709              }
  710          }
  711      }
  712  
  713      pub fn privacy_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace)
  714                                   -> Option<Privacy> {
  715          match namespace {
  716              TypeNS => {
  717                  match self.type_def {
  718                      None => None,
  719                      Some(ref type_def) => Some((*type_def).privacy)
  720                  }
  721              }
  722              ValueNS => {
  723                  match self.value_def {
  724                      None => None,
  725                      Some(value_def) => Some(value_def.privacy)
  726                  }
  727              }
  728          }
  729      }
  730  
  731      pub fn span_for_namespace(&self, namespace: Namespace) -> Option<Span> {
  732          if self.defined_in_namespace(namespace) {
  733              match namespace {
  734                  TypeNS  => {
  735                      match self.type_def {
  736                          None => None,
  737                          Some(type_def) => type_def.type_span
  738                      }
  739                  }
  740                  ValueNS => {
  741                      match self.value_def {
  742                          None => None,
  743                          Some(value_def) => value_def.value_span
  744                      }
  745                  }
  746              }
  747          } else {
  748              None
  749          }
  750      }
  751  }
  752  
  753  pub fn NameBindings() -> NameBindings {
  754      NameBindings {
  755          type_def: None,
  756          value_def: None
  757      }
  758  }

  760  /// Interns the names of the primitive types.

  763  }

  767                    string: &str,
  768                    primitive_type: prim_ty) {
  769          self.primitive_types.insert(token::intern(string), primitive_type);
  770      }

  773  pub fn PrimitiveTypeTable() -> PrimitiveTypeTable {
  774      let mut table = PrimitiveTypeTable {
  775          primitive_types: HashMap::new()
  776      };
  777  
  778      table.intern("bool",    ty_bool);

  780      table.intern("float",   ty_float(ty_f));
  781      table.intern("f32",     ty_float(ty_f32));
  782      table.intern("f64",     ty_float(ty_f64));
  783      table.intern("int",     ty_int(ty_i));
  784      table.intern("i8",      ty_int(ty_i8));
  785      table.intern("i16",     ty_int(ty_i16));
  786      table.intern("i32",     ty_int(ty_i32));
  787      table.intern("i64",     ty_int(ty_i64));
  788      table.intern("str",     ty_str);
  789      table.intern("uint",    ty_uint(ty_u));
  790      table.intern("u8",      ty_uint(ty_u8));
  791      table.intern("u16",     ty_uint(ty_u16));
  792      table.intern("u32",     ty_uint(ty_u32));
  793      table.intern("u64",     ty_uint(ty_u64));
  794  
  795      return table;
  796  }

  799  pub fn namespace_error_to_str(ns: NamespaceError) -> &'static str {
  800      match ns {

  807  
  808  pub fn Resolver(session: Session,
  809                  lang_items: LanguageItems,
  810                  crate: @Crate)
  811               -> Resolver {
  812      let graph_root = @mut NameBindings();
  813  
  814      graph_root.define_module(Public,
  815                               NoParentLink,
  816                               Some(DefId { crate: 0, node: 0 }),
  817                               NormalModuleKind,
  818                               false,
  819                               crate.span);
  820  
  821      let current_module = graph_root.get_module();
  822  
  823      let this = Resolver {
  824          session: @session,
  825          lang_items: lang_items,
  826          crate: crate,
  827  
  828          // The outermost module has def ID 0; this is not reflected in the
  829          // AST.
  830  
  831          graph_root: graph_root,
  832  
  833          method_map: @mut HashMap::new(),
  834          structs: HashSet::new(),
  835  
  836          unresolved_imports: 0,
  837  
  838          current_module: current_module,
  839          value_ribs: @mut ~[],
  840          type_ribs: @mut ~[],
  841          label_ribs: @mut ~[],
  842  
  843          xray_context: NoXray,
  844          current_trait_refs: None,
  845  
  846          self_ident: special_idents::self_,
  847          type_self_ident: special_idents::type_self,
  848  
  849          primitive_type_table: @PrimitiveTypeTable(),
  850  
  851          namespaces: ~[ TypeNS, ValueNS ],
  852  
  853          def_map: @mut HashMap::new(),
  854          export_map2: @mut HashMap::new(),
  855          trait_map: HashMap::new(),
  856          used_imports: HashSet::new(),
  857  
  858          emit_errors: true,
  859          intr: session.intr()
  860      };
  861  
  862      this
  863  }
  864  
  865  /// The main resolver class.
  866  pub struct Resolver {
  867      session: @Session,
  868      lang_items: LanguageItems,
  869      crate: @Crate,
  870  
  871      intr: @ident_interner,
  872  
  873      graph_root: @mut NameBindings,
  874  
  875      method_map: @mut HashMap<Name, HashSet<DefId>>,
  876      structs: HashSet<DefId>,
  877  
  878      // The number of imports that are currently unresolved.
  879      unresolved_imports: uint,
  880  
  881      // The module that represents the current item scope.
  882      current_module: @mut Module,
  883  
  884      // The current set of local scopes, for values.
  885      // FIXME #4948: Reuse ribs to avoid allocation.
  886      value_ribs: @mut ~[@Rib],
  887  
  888      // The current set of local scopes, for types.
  889      type_ribs: @mut ~[@Rib],
  890  
  891      // The current set of local scopes, for labels.
  892      label_ribs: @mut ~[@Rib],
  893  
  894      // Whether the current context is an X-ray context. An X-ray context is
  895      // allowed to access private names of any module.
  896      xray_context: XrayFlag,
  897  
  898      // The trait that the current context can refer to.
  899      current_trait_refs: Option<~[DefId]>,
  900  
  901      // The ident for the keyword "self".
  902      self_ident: Ident,
  903      // The ident for the non-keyword "Self".
  904      type_self_ident: Ident,
  905  
  906      // The idents for the primitive types.
  907      primitive_type_table: @PrimitiveTypeTable,
  908  
  909      // The four namespaces.
  910      namespaces: ~[Namespace],
  911  
  912      def_map: DefMap,
  913      export_map2: ExportMap2,
  914      trait_map: TraitMap,
  915  
  916      // Whether or not to print error messages. Can be set to true
  917      // when getting additional info for error message suggestions,
  918      // so as to avoid printing duplicate errors
  919      emit_errors: bool,
  920  
  921      used_imports: HashSet<NodeId>,
  922  }
  923  
  924  struct BuildReducedGraphVisitor {
  925      resolver: @mut Resolver,
  926  }
  927  
  928  impl Visitor<ReducedGraphParent> for BuildReducedGraphVisitor {
  929  
  930      fn visit_item(&mut self, item:@item, context:ReducedGraphParent) {
  931          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_item(item, (context, self));
  932      }
  933  
  934      fn visit_foreign_item(&mut self, foreign_item:@foreign_item, context:ReducedGraphParent) {
  935          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_foreign_item(foreign_item,
  936                                                               (context,
  937                                                                self));
  938      }
  939  
  940      fn visit_view_item(&mut self, view_item:&view_item, context:ReducedGraphParent) {
  941          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_view_item(view_item,
  942                                                            (context,
  943                                                             self));
  944      }
  945  
  946      fn visit_block(&mut self, block:&Block, context:ReducedGraphParent) {
  947          self.resolver.build_reduced_graph_for_block(block,
  948                                                        (context,
  949                                                         self));
  950      }
  951  
  952  }
  953  
  954  struct UnusedImportCheckVisitor { resolver: @mut Resolver }
  955  
  956  impl Visitor<()> for UnusedImportCheckVisitor {
  957      fn visit_view_item(&mut self, vi:&view_item, _:()) {
  958          self.resolver.check_for_item_unused_imports(vi);
  959          visit::walk_view_item(self, vi, ());
  960      }
  961  }
  962  
  963  impl Resolver {
  964      /// The main name resolution procedure.
  965      pub fn resolve(@mut self) {
  966          self.build_reduced_graph();
  967          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  968  
  969          self.resolve_imports();
  970          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  971  
  972          self.record_exports();
  973          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  974  
  975          self.resolve_crate();
  976          self.session.abort_if_errors();
  977  
  978          self.check_for_unused_imports();
  979      }
  980  
  981      //
  982      // Reduced graph building
  983      //
  984      // Here we build the "reduced graph": the graph of the module tree without
  985      // any imports resolved.
  986      //
  987  
  988      /// Constructs the reduced graph for the entire crate.
  989      pub fn build_reduced_graph(@mut self) {
  990          let initial_parent =
  991              ModuleReducedGraphParent(self.graph_root.get_module());
  992  
  993          let mut visitor = BuildReducedGraphVisitor { resolver: self, };
  994          visit::walk_crate(&mut visitor, self.crate, initial_parent);
  995      }
  996  
  997      /// Returns the current module tracked by the reduced graph parent.
  998      pub fn get_module_from_parent(@mut self,
  999                                    reduced_graph_parent: ReducedGraphParent)
 1000                                    -> @mut Module {
 1001          match reduced_graph_parent {
 1002              ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_) => {
 1003                  return module_;
 1004              }
 1005          }
 1006      }
 1007  
 1008      /**
 1009       * Adds a new child item to the module definition of the parent node and
 1010       * returns its corresponding name bindings as well as the current parent.
 1011       * Or, if we're inside a block, creates (or reuses) an anonymous module
 1012       * corresponding to the innermost block ID and returns the name bindings
 1013       * as well as the newly-created parent.
 1014       *
 1015       * If this node does not have a module definition and we are not inside
 1016       * a block, fails.
 1017       */
 1018      pub fn add_child(@mut self,
 1019                       name: Ident,
 1020                       reduced_graph_parent: ReducedGraphParent,
 1021                       duplicate_checking_mode: DuplicateCheckingMode,
 1022                       // For printing errors
 1023                       sp: Span)
 1024                       -> (@mut NameBindings, ReducedGraphParent) {
 1025          // If this is the immediate descendant of a module, then we add the
 1026          // child name directly. Otherwise, we create or reuse an anonymous
 1027          // module and add the child to that.
 1028  
 1029          let module_;
 1030          match reduced_graph_parent {
 1031              ModuleReducedGraphParent(parent_module) => {
 1032                  module_ = parent_module;
 1033              }
 1034          }
 1035  
 1036          // Add or reuse the child.
 1037          let new_parent = ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_);
 1038          match module_.children.find(&name.name) {
 1039              None => {
 1040                  let child = @mut NameBindings();
 1041                  module_.children.insert(name.name, child);
 1042                  return (child, new_parent);
 1043              }
 1044              Some(&child) => {
 1045                  // Enforce the duplicate checking mode:
 1046                  //
 1047                  // * If we're requesting duplicate module checking, check that
 1048                  //   there isn't a module in the module with the same name.
 1049                  //
 1050                  // * If we're requesting duplicate type checking, check that
 1051                  //   there isn't a type in the module with the same name.
 1052                  //
 1053                  // * If we're requesting duplicate value checking, check that
 1054                  //   there isn't a value in the module with the same name.
 1055                  //
 1056                  // * If we're requesting duplicate type checking and duplicate
 1057                  //   value checking, check that there isn't a duplicate type
 1058                  //   and a duplicate value with the same name.
 1059                  //
 1060                  // * If no duplicate checking was requested at all, do
 1061                  //   nothing.
 1062  
 1063                  let mut duplicate_type = NoError;
 1064                  let ns = match duplicate_checking_mode {
 1065                      ForbidDuplicateModules => {
 1066                          if (child.get_module_if_available().is_some()) {
 1067                              duplicate_type = ModuleError;
 1068                          }
 1069                          Some(TypeNS)
 1070                      }
 1071                      ForbidDuplicateTypes => {
 1072                          match child.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 1073                              Some(DefMod(_)) | None => {}
 1074                              Some(_) => duplicate_type = TypeError
 1075                          }
 1076                          Some(TypeNS)
 1077                      }
 1078                      ForbidDuplicateValues => {
 1079                          if child.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 1080                              duplicate_type = ValueError;
 1081                          }
 1082                          Some(ValueNS)
 1083                      }
 1084                      ForbidDuplicateTypesAndValues => {
 1085                          let mut n = None;
 1086                          match child.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 1087                              Some(DefMod(_)) | None => {}
 1088                              Some(_) => {
 1089                                  n = Some(TypeNS);
 1090                                  duplicate_type = TypeError;
 1091                              }
 1092                          };
 1093                          if child.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 1094                              duplicate_type = ValueError;
 1095                              n = Some(ValueNS);
 1096                          }
 1097                          n
 1098                      }
 1099                      OverwriteDuplicates => None
 1100                  };
 1101                  if (duplicate_type != NoError) {
 1102                      // Return an error here by looking up the namespace that
 1103                      // had the duplicate.
 1104                      let ns = ns.unwrap();
 1105                      self.resolve_error(sp,
 1106                          fmt!("duplicate definition of %s `%s`",
 1107                               namespace_error_to_str(duplicate_type),
 1108                               self.session.str_of(name)));
 1109                      {
 1110                          let r = child.span_for_namespace(ns);
 1111                          for sp in r.iter() {
 1112                              self.session.span_note(*sp,
 1113                                   fmt!("first definition of %s `%s` here",
 1114                                        namespace_error_to_str(duplicate_type),
 1115                                        self.session.str_of(name)));
 1116                          }
 1117                      }
 1118                  }
 1119                  return (child, new_parent);
 1120              }
 1121          }
 1122      }
 1123  
 1124      pub fn block_needs_anonymous_module(@mut self, block: &Block) -> bool {
 1125          // If the block has view items, we need an anonymous module.
 1126          if block.view_items.len() > 0 {
 1127              return true;
 1128          }
 1129  
 1130          // Check each statement.
 1131          for statement in block.stmts.iter() {
 1132              match statement.node {
 1133                  StmtDecl(declaration, _) => {
 1134                      match declaration.node {
 1135                          DeclItem(_) => {
 1136                              return true;
 1137                          }
 1138                          _ => {
 1139                              // Keep searching.
 1140                          }
 1141                      }
 1142                  }
 1143                  _ => {
 1144                      // Keep searching.
 1145                  }
 1146              }
 1147          }
 1148  
 1149          // If we found neither view items nor items, we don't need to create
 1150          // an anonymous module.
 1151  
 1152          return false;
 1153      }
 1154  
 1155      pub fn get_parent_link(@mut self, parent: ReducedGraphParent, name: Ident)
 1156                             -> ParentLink {
 1157          match parent {
 1158              ModuleReducedGraphParent(module_) => {
 1159                  return ModuleParentLink(module_, name);
 1160              }
 1161          }
 1162      }
 1163  
 1164      /// Constructs the reduced graph for one item.
 1165      pub fn build_reduced_graph_for_item(@mut self,
 1166                                          item: @item,
 1167                                          (parent, visitor): (ReducedGraphParent,
 1168                                                              &mut BuildReducedGraphVisitor)) {
 1169          let ident = item.ident;
 1170          let sp = item.span;
 1171          let privacy = visibility_to_privacy(item.vis);
 1172  
 1173          match item.node {
 1174              item_mod(ref module_) => {
 1175                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1176                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateModules, sp);
 1177  
 1178                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1179                  let def_id = DefId { crate: 0, node: item.id };
 1180                  name_bindings.define_module(privacy,
 1181                                              parent_link,
 1182                                              Some(def_id),
 1183                                              NormalModuleKind,
 1184                                              false,
 1185                                              sp);
 1186  
 1187                  let new_parent =
 1188                      ModuleReducedGraphParent(name_bindings.get_module());
 1189  
 1190                  visit::walk_mod(visitor, module_, new_parent);
 1191              }
 1192  
 1193              item_foreign_mod(ref fm) => {
 1194                  let new_parent = match fm.sort {
 1195                      named => {
 1196                          let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1197                              self.add_child(ident, parent,
 1198                                             ForbidDuplicateModules, sp);
 1199  
 1200                          let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent,
 1201                                                                 ident);
 1202                          let def_id = DefId { crate: 0, node: item.id };
 1203                          name_bindings.define_module(privacy,
 1204                                                      parent_link,
 1205                                                      Some(def_id),
 1206                                                      ExternModuleKind,
 1207                                                      false,
 1208                                                      sp);
 1209  
 1210                          ModuleReducedGraphParent(name_bindings.get_module())
 1211                      }
 1212  
 1213                      // For anon foreign mods, the contents just go in the
 1214                      // current scope
 1215                      anonymous => parent
 1216                  };
 1217  
 1218                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, new_parent);
 1219              }
 1220  
 1221              // These items live in the value namespace.
 1222              item_static(_, m, _) => {
 1223                  let (name_bindings, _) =
 1224                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues, sp);
 1225                  let mutbl = m == ast::MutMutable;
 1226  
 1227                  name_bindings.define_value
 1228                      (privacy, DefStatic(local_def(item.id), mutbl), sp);
 1229              }
 1230              item_fn(_, purity, _, _, _) => {
 1231                let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1232                  self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues, sp);
 1233  
 1234                  let def = DefFn(local_def(item.id), purity);
 1235                  name_bindings.define_value(privacy, def, sp);
 1236                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, new_parent);
 1237              }
 1238  
 1239              // These items live in the type namespace.
 1240              item_ty(*) => {
 1241                  let (name_bindings, _) =
 1242                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1243  
 1244                  name_bindings.define_type
 1245                      (privacy, DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp);
 1246              }
 1247  
 1248              item_enum(ref enum_definition, _) => {
 1249                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1250                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1251  
 1252                  name_bindings.define_type
 1253                      (privacy, DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp);
 1254  
 1255                  for variant in (*enum_definition).variants.iter() {
 1256                      self.build_reduced_graph_for_variant(
 1257                          variant,
 1258                          local_def(item.id),
 1259                          // inherited => privacy of the enum item
 1260                          variant_visibility_to_privacy(variant.node.vis,
 1261                                                        privacy == Public),
 1262                          new_parent, visitor);
 1263                  }
 1264              }
 1265  
 1266              // These items live in both the type and value namespaces.
 1267              item_struct(struct_def, _) => {
 1268                  // Adding to both Type and Value namespaces or just Type?
 1269                  let (forbid, ctor_id) = match struct_def.ctor_id {
 1270                      Some(ctor_id)   => (ForbidDuplicateTypesAndValues, Some(ctor_id)),
 1271                      None            => (ForbidDuplicateTypes, None)
 1272                  };
 1273  
 1274                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) = self.add_child(ident, parent, forbid, sp);
 1275  
 1276                  // Define a name in the type namespace.
 1277                  name_bindings.define_type(privacy, DefTy(local_def(item.id)), sp);
 1278  
 1279                  // If this is a newtype or unit-like struct, define a name
 1280                  // in the value namespace as well
 1281                  do ctor_id.while_some |cid| {
 1282                      name_bindings.define_value(privacy, DefStruct(local_def(cid)), sp);
 1283                      None
 1284                  }
 1285  
 1286                  // Record the def ID of this struct.
 1287                  self.structs.insert(local_def(item.id));
 1288  
 1289                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, new_parent);
 1290              }
 1291  
 1292              item_impl(_, None, ref ty, ref methods) => {
 1293                  // If this implements an anonymous trait, then add all the
 1294                  // methods within to a new module, if the type was defined
 1295                  // within this module.
 1296                  //
 1297                  // FIXME (#3785): This is quite unsatisfactory. Perhaps we
 1298                  // should modify anonymous traits to only be implementable in
 1299                  // the same module that declared the type.
 1300  
 1301                  // Create the module and add all methods.
 1302                  match ty {
 1303                      &Ty {
 1304                          node: ty_path(ref path, _, _),
 1305                          _
 1306                      } if path.segments.len() == 1 => {
 1307                          let name = path_to_ident(path);
 1308  
 1309                          let new_parent = match parent.children.find(&name.name) {
 1310                              // It already exists
 1311                              Some(&child) if child.get_module_if_available()
 1312                                                   .is_some() &&
 1313                                              child.get_module().kind ==
 1314                                                  ImplModuleKind => {
 1315                                  ModuleReducedGraphParent(child.get_module())
 1316                              }
 1317                              // Create the module
 1318                              _ => {
 1319                                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1320                                      self.add_child(name,
 1321                                                     parent,
 1322                                                     ForbidDuplicateModules,
 1323                                                     sp);
 1324  
 1325                                  let parent_link =
 1326                                      self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1327                                  let def_id = local_def(item.id);
 1328                                  name_bindings.define_module(Public,
 1329                                                              parent_link,
 1330                                                              Some(def_id),
 1331                                                              ImplModuleKind,
 1332                                                              false,
 1333                                                              sp);
 1334  
 1335                                  ModuleReducedGraphParent(
 1336                                      name_bindings.get_module())
 1337                              }
 1338                          };
 1339  
 1340                          // For each method...
 1341                          for method in methods.iter() {
 1342                              // Add the method to the module.
 1343                              let ident = method.ident;
 1344                              let (method_name_bindings, _) =
 1345                                  self.add_child(ident,
 1346                                                 new_parent,
 1347                                                 ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1348                                                 method.span);
 1349                              let def = match method.explicit_self.node {
 1350                                  sty_static => {
 1351                                      // Static methods become
 1352                                      // `def_static_method`s.
 1353                                      DefStaticMethod(local_def(method.id),
 1354                                                        FromImpl(local_def(
 1355                                                          item.id)),
 1356                                                        method.purity)
 1357                                  }
 1358                                  _ => {
 1359                                      // Non-static methods become
 1360                                      // `def_method`s.
 1361                                      DefMethod(local_def(method.id), None)
 1362                                  }
 1363                              };
 1364  
 1365                              method_name_bindings.define_value(Public,
 1366                                                                def,
 1367                                                                method.span);
 1368                          }
 1369                      }
 1370                      _ => {}
 1371                  }
 1372  
 1373                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, parent);
 1374              }
 1375  
 1376              item_impl(_, Some(_), _, _) => {
 1377                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, parent);
 1378              }
 1379  
 1380              item_trait(_, _, ref methods) => {
 1381                  let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1382                      self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypes, sp);
 1383  
 1384                  // Add all the methods within to a new module.
 1385                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(parent, ident);
 1386                  name_bindings.define_module(privacy,
 1387                                              parent_link,
 1388                                              Some(local_def(item.id)),
 1389                                              TraitModuleKind,
 1390                                              false,
 1391                                              sp);
 1392                  let module_parent = ModuleReducedGraphParent(name_bindings.
 1393                                                               get_module());
 1394  
 1395                  // Add the names of all the methods to the trait info.
 1396                  let mut method_names = HashMap::new();
 1397                  for method in methods.iter() {
 1398                      let ty_m = trait_method_to_ty_method(method);
 1399  
 1400                      let ident = ty_m.ident;
 1401  
 1402                      // Add it as a name in the trait module.
 1403                      let def = match ty_m.explicit_self.node {
 1404                          sty_static => {
 1405                              // Static methods become `def_static_method`s.
 1406                              DefStaticMethod(local_def(ty_m.id),
 1407                                                FromTrait(local_def(item.id)),
 1408                                                ty_m.purity)
 1409                          }
 1410                          _ => {
 1411                              // Non-static methods become `def_method`s.
 1412                              DefMethod(local_def(ty_m.id),
 1413                                         Some(local_def(item.id)))
 1414                          }
 1415                      };
 1416  
 1417                      let (method_name_bindings, _) =
 1418                          self.add_child(ident,
 1419                                         module_parent,
 1420                                         ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1421                                         ty_m.span);
 1422                      method_name_bindings.define_value(Public, def, ty_m.span);
 1423  
 1424                      // Add it to the trait info if not static.
 1425                      match ty_m.explicit_self.node {
 1426                          sty_static => {}
 1427                          _ => {
 1428                              method_names.insert(ident.name, ());
 1429                          }
 1430                      }
 1431                  }
 1432  
 1433                  let def_id = local_def(item.id);
 1434                  for (name, _) in method_names.iter() {
 1435                      if !self.method_map.contains_key(name) {
 1436                          self.method_map.insert(*name, HashSet::new());
 1437                      }
 1438                      match self.method_map.find_mut(name) {
 1439                          Some(s) => { s.insert(def_id); },
 1440                          _ => fail!("Can't happen"),
 1441                      }
 1442                  }
 1443  
 1444                  name_bindings.define_type(privacy, DefTrait(def_id), sp);
 1445                  visit::walk_item(visitor, item, new_parent);
 1446              }
 1447  
 1448              item_mac(*) => {
 1449                  fail!("item macros unimplemented")
 1450              }
 1451          }
 1452      }
 1453  
 1454      // Constructs the reduced graph for one variant. Variants exist in the
 1455      // type and/or value namespaces.
 1456      pub fn build_reduced_graph_for_variant(@mut self,
 1457                                             variant: &variant,
 1458                                             item_id: DefId,
 1459                                             parent_privacy: Privacy,
 1460                                             parent: ReducedGraphParent,
 1461                                             _: &mut BuildReducedGraphVisitor) {
 1462          let ident = variant.node.name;
 1463  
 1464          let privacy =
 1465              match variant.node.vis {
 1466                  public    => Public,
 1467                  private   => Private,
 1468                  inherited => parent_privacy
 1469              };
 1470  
 1471          match variant.node.kind {
 1472              tuple_variant_kind(_) => {
 1473                  let (child, _) = self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1474                                                  variant.span);
 1475                  child.define_value(privacy,
 1476                                     DefVariant(item_id,
 1477                                                 local_def(variant.node.id), false),
 1478                                     variant.span);
 1479              }
 1480              struct_variant_kind(_) => {
 1481                  let (child, _) = self.add_child(ident, parent, ForbidDuplicateTypesAndValues,
 1482                                                  variant.span);
 1483                  child.define_type(privacy,
 1484                                    DefVariant(item_id,
 1485                                                local_def(variant.node.id), true),
 1486                                    variant.span);
 1487                  self.structs.insert(local_def(variant.node.id));
 1488              }
 1489          }
 1490      }

 1492      /// Constructs the reduced graph for one 'view item'. View items consist
 1493      /// of imports and use directives.
 1494      pub fn build_reduced_graph_for_view_item(@mut self,
 1495                                               view_item: &view_item,
 1496                                               (parent, _):
 1497                                               (ReducedGraphParent,
 1498                                                &mut BuildReducedGraphVisitor)) {
 1499          let privacy = visibility_to_privacy(view_item.vis);
 1500          match view_item.node {
 1501              view_item_use(ref view_paths) => {
 1502                  for view_path in view_paths.iter() {
 1503                      // Extract and intern the module part of the path. For
 1504                      // globs and lists, the path is found directly in the AST;
 1505                      // for simple paths we have to munge the path a little.
 1506  
 1507                      let mut module_path = ~[];
 1508                      match view_path.node {
 1509                          view_path_simple(_, ref full_path, _) => {
 1510                              let path_len = full_path.segments.len();
 1511                              assert!(path_len != 0);
 1512  
 1513                              for (i, segment) in full_path.segments
 1514                                                           .iter()
 1515                                                           .enumerate() {
 1516                                  if i != path_len - 1 {
 1517                                      module_path.push(segment.identifier)
 1518                                  }
 1519                              }
 1520                          }
 1521  
 1522                          view_path_glob(ref module_ident_path, _) |
 1523                          view_path_list(ref module_ident_path, _, _) => {
 1524                              for segment in module_ident_path.segments.iter() {
 1525                                  module_path.push(segment.identifier)
 1526                              }
 1527                          }
 1528                      }
 1529  
 1530                      // Build up the import directives.
 1531                      let module_ = self.get_module_from_parent(parent);
 1532                      match view_path.node {
 1533                          view_path_simple(binding, ref full_path, id) => {
 1534                              let source_ident =
 1535                                  full_path.segments.last().identifier;
 1536                              let subclass = @SingleImport(binding,
 1537                                                           source_ident);
 1538                              self.build_import_directive(privacy,
 1539                                                          module_,
 1540                                                          module_path,
 1541                                                          subclass,
 1542                                                          view_path.span,
 1543                                                          id);
 1544                          }
 1545                          view_path_list(_, ref source_idents, _) => {
 1546                              for source_ident in source_idents.iter() {
 1547                                  let name = source_ident.node.name;
 1548                                  let subclass = @SingleImport(name, name);
 1549                                  self.build_import_directive(
 1550                                      privacy,
 1551                                      module_,
 1552                                      module_path.clone(),
 1553                                      subclass,
 1554                                      source_ident.span,
 1555                                      source_ident.node.id);
 1556                              }
 1557                          }
 1558                          view_path_glob(_, id) => {
 1559                              self.build_import_directive(privacy,
 1560                                                          module_,
 1561                                                          module_path,
 1562                                                          @GlobImport,
 1563                                                          view_path.span,
 1564                                                          id);
 1565                          }
 1566                      }
 1567                  }
 1568              }
 1569  
 1570              view_item_extern_mod(name, _, _, node_id) => {
 1571                  // n.b. we don't need to look at the path option here, because cstore already did
 1572                  match find_extern_mod_stmt_cnum(self.session.cstore,
 1573                                                          node_id) {
 1574                      Some(crate_id) => {
 1575                          let def_id = DefId { crate: crate_id, node: 0 };
 1576                          let parent_link = ModuleParentLink
 1577                              (self.get_module_from_parent(parent), name);
 1578                          let external_module = @mut Module::new(parent_link,
 1579                                                            Some(def_id),
 1580                                                            NormalModuleKind,
 1581                                                            false);
 1582  
 1583                          parent.external_module_children.insert(
 1584                              name.name,
 1585                              external_module);
 1586  
 1587                          self.build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate(
 1588                              external_module);
 1589                      }
 1590                      None => {}  // Ignore.
 1591                  }
 1592              }
 1593          }
 1594      }
 1595  
 1596      /// Constructs the reduced graph for one foreign item.
 1597      pub fn build_reduced_graph_for_foreign_item(@mut self,
 1598                                                  foreign_item: @foreign_item,
 1599                                                  (parent, visitor):
 1600                                                  (ReducedGraphParent,
 1601                                                   &mut BuildReducedGraphVisitor)) {
 1602          let name = foreign_item.ident;
 1603          let (name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1604              self.add_child(name, parent, ForbidDuplicateValues,
 1605                             foreign_item.span);
 1606  
 1607          match foreign_item.node {
 1608              foreign_item_fn(_, ref generics) => {
 1609                  let def = DefFn(local_def(foreign_item.id), unsafe_fn);
 1610                  name_bindings.define_value(Public, def, foreign_item.span);
 1611  
 1612                  do self.with_type_parameter_rib(
 1613                      HasTypeParameters(
 1614                          generics, foreign_item.id, 0, NormalRibKind))
 1615                  {
 1616                      visit::walk_foreign_item(visitor, foreign_item, new_parent);
 1617                  }
 1618              }
 1619              foreign_item_static(_, m) => {
 1620                  let def = DefStatic(local_def(foreign_item.id), m);
 1621                  name_bindings.define_value(Public, def, foreign_item.span);
 1622  
 1623                  visit::walk_foreign_item(visitor, foreign_item, new_parent);
 1624              }
 1625          }
 1626      }

 1628      pub fn build_reduced_graph_for_block(@mut self,
 1629                                           block: &Block,
 1630                                           (parent, visitor):
 1631                                           (ReducedGraphParent,
 1632                                            &mut BuildReducedGraphVisitor)) {
 1633          let new_parent;
 1634          if self.block_needs_anonymous_module(block) {
 1635              let block_id = block.id;
 1636  
 1637              debug!("(building reduced graph for block) creating a new \
 1638                      anonymous module for block %d",
 1639                     block_id);
 1640  
 1641              let parent_module = self.get_module_from_parent(parent);
 1642              let new_module = @mut Module::new(
 1643                  BlockParentLink(parent_module, block_id),
 1644                  None,
 1645                  AnonymousModuleKind,
 1646                  false);
 1647              parent_module.anonymous_children.insert(block_id, new_module);
 1648              new_parent = ModuleReducedGraphParent(new_module);
 1649          } else {
 1650              new_parent = parent;
 1651          }
 1652  
 1653          visit::walk_block(visitor, block, new_parent);
 1654      }
 1655  
 1656      fn handle_external_def(@mut self,
 1657                             def: Def,
 1658                             visibility: ast::visibility,
 1659                             child_name_bindings: @mut NameBindings,
 1660                             final_ident: &str,
 1661                             ident: Ident,
 1662                             new_parent: ReducedGraphParent) {
 1663          let privacy = visibility_to_privacy(visibility);
 1664          match def {
 1665            DefMod(def_id) | DefForeignMod(def_id) | DefStruct(def_id) |
 1666            DefTy(def_id) => {
 1667              match child_name_bindings.type_def {
 1668                Some(TypeNsDef { module_def: Some(module_def), _ }) => {
 1669                  debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) \
 1670                          already created module");
 1671                  module_def.def_id = Some(def_id);
 1672                }
 1673                Some(_) | None => {
 1674                  debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1675                          external crate) building module \
 1676                          %s", final_ident);
 1677                  let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1678  
 1679                  child_name_bindings.define_module(privacy,
 1680                                                    parent_link,
 1681                                                    Some(def_id),
 1682                                                    NormalModuleKind,
 1683                                                    true,
 1684                                                    dummy_sp());
 1685                }
 1686              }
 1687            }
 1688            _ => {}
 1689          }
 1690  
 1691          match def {
 1692            DefMod(_) | DefForeignMod(_) => {}
 1693            DefVariant(_, variant_id, is_struct) => {
 1694              debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) building \
 1695                      variant %s",
 1696                     final_ident);
 1697              // We assume the parent is visible, or else we wouldn't have seen
 1698              // it.
 1699              let privacy = variant_visibility_to_privacy(visibility, true);
 1700              if is_struct {
 1701                  child_name_bindings.define_type(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1702                  self.structs.insert(variant_id);
 1703              }
 1704              else {
 1705                  child_name_bindings.define_value(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1706              }
 1707            }
 1708            DefFn(*) | DefStaticMethod(*) | DefStatic(*) => {
 1709              debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1710                      crate) building value (fn/static) %s", final_ident);
 1711              child_name_bindings.define_value(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1712            }
 1713            DefTrait(def_id) => {
 1714                debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1715                        crate) building type %s", final_ident);
 1716  
 1717                // If this is a trait, add all the method names
 1718                // to the trait info.
 1719  
 1720                let method_def_ids =
 1721                  get_trait_method_def_ids(self.session.cstore, def_id);
 1722                let mut interned_method_names = HashSet::new();
 1723                for &method_def_id in method_def_ids.iter() {
 1724                    let (method_name, explicit_self) =
 1725                        get_method_name_and_explicit_self(self.session.cstore,
 1726                                                          method_def_id);
 1727  
 1728                    debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1729                            external crate) ... adding \
 1730                            trait method '%s'",
 1731                           self.session.str_of(method_name));
 1732  
 1733                    // Add it to the trait info if not static.
 1734                    if explicit_self != sty_static {
 1735                        interned_method_names.insert(method_name.name);
 1736                    }
 1737                }
 1738                for name in interned_method_names.iter() {
 1739                    if !self.method_map.contains_key(name) {
 1740                        self.method_map.insert(*name, HashSet::new());
 1741                    }
 1742                    match self.method_map.find_mut(name) {
 1743                        Some(s) => { s.insert(def_id); },
 1744                        _ => fail!("Can't happen"),
 1745                    }
 1746                }
 1747  
 1748                child_name_bindings.define_type(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1749  
 1750                // Define a module if necessary.
 1751                let parent_link = self.get_parent_link(new_parent, ident);
 1752                child_name_bindings.set_module_kind(privacy,
 1753                                                    parent_link,
 1754                                                    Some(def_id),
 1755                                                    TraitModuleKind,
 1756                                                    true,
 1757                                                    dummy_sp())
 1758            }
 1759            DefTy(_) => {
 1760                debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1761                        crate) building type %s", final_ident);
 1762  
 1763                child_name_bindings.define_type(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1764            }
 1765            DefStruct(def_id) => {
 1766              debug!("(building reduced graph for external \
 1767                      crate) building type and value for %s",
 1768                     final_ident);
 1769              child_name_bindings.define_type(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1770              if get_struct_fields(self.session.cstore, def_id).len() == 0 {
 1771                  child_name_bindings.define_value(privacy, def, dummy_sp());
 1772              }
 1773              self.structs.insert(def_id);
 1774            }
 1775            DefMethod(*) => {
 1776              // Ignored; handled elsewhere.
 1777            }
 1778            DefSelf(*) | DefArg(*) | DefLocal(*) |
 1779            DefPrimTy(*) | DefTyParam(*) | DefBinding(*) |
 1780            DefUse(*) | DefUpvar(*) | DefRegion(*) |
 1781            DefTyParamBinder(*) | DefLabel(*) | DefSelfTy(*) => {
 1782              fail!("didn't expect `%?`", def);
 1783            }
 1784          }
 1785      }
 1786  
 1787      /// Builds the reduced graph for a single item in an external crate.
 1788      fn build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate_def(@mut self,
 1789                                                    root: @mut Module,
 1790                                                    def_like: DefLike,
 1791                                                    ident: Ident) {
 1792          match def_like {
 1793              DlDef(def) => {
 1794                  // Add the new child item, if necessary.
 1795                  match def {
 1796                      DefForeignMod(def_id) => {
 1797                          // Foreign modules have no names. Recur and populate
 1798                          // eagerly.
 1799                          do csearch::each_child_of_item(self.session.cstore,
 1800                                                         def_id)
 1801                                  |def_like, child_ident| {
 1802                              self.build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate_def(
 1803                                  root,
 1804                                  def_like,
 1805                                  child_ident)
 1806                          }
 1807                      }
 1808                      _ => {
 1809                          let (child_name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1810                              self.add_child(ident,
 1811                                             ModuleReducedGraphParent(root),
 1812                                             OverwriteDuplicates,
 1813                                             dummy_sp());
 1814  
 1815                          self.handle_external_def(def,
 1816                                                   public,
 1817                                                   child_name_bindings,
 1818                                                   self.session.str_of(ident),
 1819                                                   ident,
 1820                                                   new_parent);
 1821                      }
 1822                  }
 1823              }
 1824              DlImpl(def) => {
 1825                  // We only process static methods of impls here.
 1826                  match get_type_name_if_impl(self.session.cstore, def) {
 1827                      None => {}
 1828                      Some(final_ident) => {
 1829                          let static_methods_opt =
 1830                              get_static_methods_if_impl(self.session.cstore,
 1831                                                         def);
 1832                          match static_methods_opt {
 1833                              Some(ref static_methods) if
 1834                                  static_methods.len() >= 1 => {
 1835                                  debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1836                                          external crate) processing \
 1837                                          static methods for type name %s",
 1838                                          self.session.str_of(
 1839                                              final_ident));
 1840  
 1841                                  let (child_name_bindings, new_parent) =
 1842                                      self.add_child(
 1843                                          final_ident,
 1844                                          ModuleReducedGraphParent(root),
 1845                                          OverwriteDuplicates,
 1846                                          dummy_sp());
 1847  
 1848                                  // Process the static methods. First,
 1849                                  // create the module.
 1850                                  let type_module;
 1851                                  match child_name_bindings.type_def {
 1852                                      Some(TypeNsDef {
 1853                                          module_def: Some(module_def),
 1854                                          _
 1855                                      }) => {
 1856                                          // We already have a module. This
 1857                                          // is OK.
 1858                                          type_module = module_def;
 1859  
 1860                                          // Mark it as an impl module if
 1861                                          // necessary.
 1862                                          type_module.kind = ImplModuleKind;
 1863                                      }
 1864                                      Some(_) | None => {
 1865                                          let parent_link =
 1866                                              self.get_parent_link(new_parent,
 1867                                                                   final_ident);
 1868                                          child_name_bindings.define_module(
 1869                                              Public,
 1870                                              parent_link,
 1871                                              Some(def),
 1872                                              ImplModuleKind,
 1873                                              true,
 1874                                              dummy_sp());
 1875                                          type_module =
 1876                                              child_name_bindings.
 1877                                                  get_module();
 1878                                      }
 1879                                  }
 1880  
 1881                                  // Add each static method to the module.
 1882                                  let new_parent =
 1883                                      ModuleReducedGraphParent(type_module);
 1884                                  for static_method_info in
 1885                                          static_methods.iter() {
 1886                                      let ident = static_method_info.ident;
 1887                                      debug!("(building reduced graph for \
 1888                                               external crate) creating \
 1889                                               static method '%s'",
 1890                                             self.session.str_of(ident));
 1891  
 1892                                      let (method_name_bindings, _) =
 1893                                          self.add_child(ident,
 1894                                                         new_parent,
 1895                                                         OverwriteDuplicates,
 1896                                                         dummy_sp());
 1897                                      let def = DefFn(
 1898                                          static_method_info.def_id,
 1899                                          static_method_info.purity);
 1900                                      method_name_bindings.define_value(
 1901                                          Public,
 1902                                          def,
 1903                                          dummy_sp());
 1904                                  }
 1905                              }
 1906  
 1907                              // Otherwise, do nothing.
 1908                              Some(_) | None => {}
 1909                          }
 1910                      }
 1911                  }
 1912              }
 1913              DlField => {
 1914                  debug!("(building reduced graph for external crate) \
 1915                          ignoring field");
 1916              }
 1917          }
 1918      }

 1920      /// Builds the reduced graph rooted at the given external module.
 1921      fn populate_external_module(@mut self, module: @mut Module) {
 1922          debug!("(populating external module) attempting to populate %s",
 1923                 self.module_to_str(module));
 1924  
 1925          let def_id = match module.def_id {
 1926              None => {
 1927                  debug!("(populating external module) ... no def ID!");
 1928                  return
 1929              }
 1930              Some(def_id) => def_id,
 1931          };
 1932  
 1933          do csearch::each_child_of_item(self.session.cstore, def_id)
 1934                  |def_like, child_ident| {
 1935              debug!("(populating external module) ... found ident: %s",
 1936                     token::ident_to_str(&child_ident));
 1937              self.build_reduced_graph_for_external_crate_def(module,
 1938                                                              def_like,
 1939                                                              child_ident)
 1940          }
 1941          module.populated = true
 1942      }
 1943  
 1944      /// Ensures that the reduced graph rooted at the given external module
 1945      /// is built, building it if it is not.
 1946      fn populate_module_if_necessary(@mut self, module: @mut Module) {
 1947          if !module.populated {
 1948              self.populate_external_module(module)
 1949          }
 1950          assert!(module.populated)
 1951      }
