 1966      /// Creates and adds an import directive to the given module.
 1967      pub fn build_import_directive(@mut self,
 1968                                    privacy: Privacy,
 1969                                    module_: @mut Module,
 1970                                    module_path: ~[Ident],
 1971                                    subclass: @ImportDirectiveSubclass,
 1972                                    span: Span,
 1973                                    id: NodeId) {
 1974          let directive = @ImportDirective::new(privacy, module_path,
 1975                                           subclass, span, id);
 1976          module_.imports.push(directive);
 1977  
 1978          // Bump the reference count on the name. Or, if this is a glob, set
 1979          // the appropriate flag.
 1980  
 1981          match *subclass {
 1982              SingleImport(target, _) => {
 1983                  debug!("(building import directive) building import \
 1984                          directive: privacy %? %s::%s",
 1985                         privacy,
 1986                         self.idents_to_str(directive.module_path),
 1987                         self.session.str_of(target));
 1988  
 1989                  match module_.import_resolutions.find(&target.name) {
 1990                      Some(&resolution) => {
 1991                          debug!("(building import directive) bumping \
 1992                                  reference");
 1993                          resolution.outstanding_references += 1;
 1994  
 1995                          // the source of this name is different now
 1996                          resolution.privacy = privacy;
 1997                          resolution.type_id = id;
 1998                          resolution.value_id = id;
 1999                      }
 2000                      None => {
 2001                          debug!("(building import directive) creating new");
 2002                          let resolution = @mut ImportResolution::new(privacy, id);
 2003                          resolution.outstanding_references = 1;
 2004                          module_.import_resolutions.insert(target.name, resolution);
 2005                      }
 2006                  }
 2007              }
 2008              GlobImport => {
 2009                  // Set the glob flag. This tells us that we don't know the
 2010                  // module's exports ahead of time.
 2011  
 2012                  module_.glob_count += 1;
 2013              }
 2014          }
 2015  
 2016          self.unresolved_imports += 1;
 2017      }
 2018  
 2019      // Import resolution
 2020      //
 2021      // This is a fixed-point algorithm. We resolve imports until our efforts
 2022      // are stymied by an unresolved import; then we bail out of the current
 2023      // module and continue. We terminate successfully once no more imports
 2024      // remain or unsuccessfully when no forward progress in resolving imports
 2025      // is made.
 2026  
 2027      /// Resolves all imports for the crate. This method performs the fixed-
 2028      /// point iteration.
 2029      pub fn resolve_imports(@mut self) {
 2030          let mut i = 0;
 2031          let mut prev_unresolved_imports = 0;
 2032          loop {
 2033              debug!("(resolving imports) iteration %u, %u imports left",
 2034                     i, self.unresolved_imports);
 2035  
 2036              let module_root = self.graph_root.get_module();
 2037              self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(module_root);
 2038  
 2039              if self.unresolved_imports == 0 {
 2040                  debug!("(resolving imports) success");
 2041                  break;
 2042              }
 2043  
 2044              if self.unresolved_imports == prev_unresolved_imports {
 2045                  self.report_unresolved_imports(module_root);
 2046                  break;
 2047              }
 2048  
 2049              i += 1;
 2050              prev_unresolved_imports = self.unresolved_imports;
 2051          }
 2052      }
 2053  
 2054      /// Attempts to resolve imports for the given module and all of its
 2055      /// submodules.
 2056      pub fn resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(@mut self,
 2057                                                module_: @mut Module) {
 2058          debug!("(resolving imports for module subtree) resolving %s",
 2059                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2060          self.resolve_imports_for_module(module_);
 2061  
 2062          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 2063          for (_, &child_node) in module_.children.iter() {
 2064              match child_node.get_module_if_available() {
 2065                  None => {
 2066                      // Nothing to do.
 2067                  }
 2068                  Some(child_module) => {
 2069                      self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 2070                  }
 2071              }
 2072          }
 2073  
 2074          for (_, &child_module) in module_.anonymous_children.iter() {
 2075              self.resolve_imports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 2076          }
 2077      }
 2078  
 2079      /// Attempts to resolve imports for the given module only.
 2080      pub fn resolve_imports_for_module(@mut self, module: @mut Module) {
 2081          if module.all_imports_resolved() {
 2082              debug!("(resolving imports for module) all imports resolved for \
 2083                     %s",
 2084                     self.module_to_str(module));
 2085              return;
 2086          }
 2087  
 2088          let imports = &mut *module.imports;
 2089          let import_count = imports.len();
 2090          while module.resolved_import_count < import_count {
 2091              let import_index = module.resolved_import_count;
 2092              let import_directive = imports[import_index];
 2093              match self.resolve_import_for_module(module, import_directive) {
 2094                  Failed => {
 2095                      // We presumably emitted an error. Continue.
 2096                      let msg = fmt!("failed to resolve import `%s`",
 2097                                     self.import_path_to_str(
 2098                                         import_directive.module_path,
 2099                                         *import_directive.subclass));
 2100                      self.resolve_error(import_directive.span, msg);
 2101                  }
 2102                  Indeterminate => {
 2103                      // Bail out. We'll come around next time.
 2104                      break;
 2105                  }
 2106                  Success(()) => {
 2107                      // Good. Continue.
 2108                  }
 2109              }
 2110  
 2111              module.resolved_import_count += 1;
 2112          }
 2113      }

 2115      pub fn idents_to_str(@mut self, idents: &[Ident]) -> ~str {
 2116          let mut first = true;
 2117          let mut result = ~"";
 2118          for ident in idents.iter() {
 2119              if first {
 2120                  first = false
 2121              } else {
 2122                  result.push_str("::")
 2123              }
 2124              result.push_str(self.session.str_of(*ident));
 2125          };

 2127      }

 2159      /// Attempts to resolve the given import. The return value indicates
 2160      /// failure if we're certain the name does not exist, indeterminate if we
 2161      /// don't know whether the name exists at the moment due to other
 2162      /// currently-unresolved imports, or success if we know the name exists.
 2163      /// If successful, the resolved bindings are written into the module.
 2164      pub fn resolve_import_for_module(@mut self,
 2165                                       module_: @mut Module,
 2166                                       import_directive: @ImportDirective)
 2167                                       -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2168          let mut resolution_result = Failed;
 2169          let module_path = &import_directive.module_path;
 2170  
 2171          debug!("(resolving import for module) resolving import `%s::...` in \
 2172                  `%s`",
 2173                 self.idents_to_str(*module_path),
 2174                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2175  
 2176          // First, resolve the module path for the directive, if necessary.
 2177          let containing_module = if module_path.len() == 0 {
 2178              // Use the crate root.
 2179              Some(self.graph_root.get_module())
 2180          } else {
 2181              match self.resolve_module_path(module_,
 2182                                             *module_path,
 2183                                             DontUseLexicalScope,
 2184                                             import_directive.span,
 2185                                             ImportSearch) {
 2186  
 2187                  Failed => None,
 2188                  Indeterminate => {
 2189                      resolution_result = Indeterminate;
 2190                      None
 2191                  }
 2192                  Success(containing_module) => Some(containing_module),
 2193              }
 2194          };
 2195  
 2196          match containing_module {
 2197              None => {}
 2198              Some(containing_module) => {
 2199                  // We found the module that the target is contained
 2200                  // within. Attempt to resolve the import within it.
 2201  
 2202                  match *import_directive.subclass {
 2203                      SingleImport(target, source) => {
 2204                          resolution_result =
 2205                              self.resolve_single_import(module_,
 2206                                                         containing_module,
 2207                                                         target,
 2208                                                         source,
 2209                                                         import_directive);
 2210                      }
 2211                      GlobImport => {
 2212                          let privacy = import_directive.privacy;
 2213                          resolution_result =
 2214                              self.resolve_glob_import(privacy,
 2215                                                       module_,
 2216                                                       containing_module,
 2217                                                       import_directive.id);
 2218                      }
 2219                  }
 2220              }
 2221          }
 2222  
 2223          // Decrement the count of unresolved imports.
 2224          match resolution_result {
 2225              Success(()) => {
 2226                  assert!(self.unresolved_imports >= 1);
 2227                  self.unresolved_imports -= 1;
 2228              }
 2229              _ => {
 2230                  // Nothing to do here; just return the error.
 2231              }
 2232          }
 2233  
 2234          // Decrement the count of unresolved globs if necessary. But only if
 2235          // the resolution result is indeterminate -- otherwise we'll stop
 2236          // processing imports here. (See the loop in
 2237          // resolve_imports_for_module.)
 2238  
 2239          if !resolution_result.indeterminate() {
 2240              match *import_directive.subclass {
 2241                  GlobImport => {
 2242                      assert!(module_.glob_count >= 1);
 2243                      module_.glob_count -= 1;
 2244                  }
 2245                  SingleImport(*) => {
 2246                      // Ignore.
 2247                  }
 2248              }
 2249          }
 2250  
 2251          return resolution_result;
 2252      }

 2254      pub fn create_name_bindings_from_module(module: @mut Module)
 2255                                              -> NameBindings {
 2256          NameBindings {
 2257              type_def: Some(TypeNsDef {
 2258                  privacy: Public,
 2259                  module_def: Some(module),
 2260                  type_def: None,
 2261                  type_span: None
 2262              }),
 2263              value_def: None,
 2264          }
 2265      }
 2266  
 2267      pub fn resolve_single_import(@mut self,
 2268                                   module_: @mut Module,
 2269                                   containing_module: @mut Module,
 2270                                   target: Ident,
 2271                                   source: Ident,
 2272                                   directive: &ImportDirective)
 2273                                   -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2274          debug!("(resolving single import) resolving `%s` = `%s::%s` from \
 2275                  `%s`",
 2276                 self.session.str_of(target),
 2277                 self.module_to_str(containing_module),
 2278                 self.session.str_of(source),
 2279                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2280  
 2281          // We need to resolve both namespaces for this to succeed.
 2282          //
 2283  
 2284          let mut value_result = UnknownResult;
 2285          let mut type_result = UnknownResult;
 2286  
 2287          // Search for direct children of the containing module.
 2288          self.populate_module_if_necessary(containing_module);
 2289          match containing_module.children.find(&source.name) {
 2290              None => {
 2291                  // Continue.
 2292              }
 2293              Some(child_name_bindings) => {
 2294                  if child_name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(ValueNS) {
 2295                      value_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2296                                                 *child_name_bindings);
 2297                  }
 2298                  if child_name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(TypeNS) {
 2299                      type_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2300                                                *child_name_bindings);
 2301                  }
 2302              }
 2303          }
 2304  
 2305          // Unless we managed to find a result in both namespaces (unlikely),
 2306          // search imports as well.
 2307          match (value_result, type_result) {
 2308              (BoundResult(*), BoundResult(*)) => {} // Continue.
 2309              _ => {
 2310                  // If there is an unresolved glob at this point in the
 2311                  // containing module, bail out. We don't know enough to be
 2312                  // able to resolve this import.
 2313  
 2314                  if containing_module.glob_count > 0 {
 2315                      debug!("(resolving single import) unresolved glob; \
 2316                              bailing out");
 2317                      return Indeterminate;
 2318                  }
 2319  
 2320                  // Now search the exported imports within the containing
 2321                  // module.
 2322  
 2323                  match containing_module.import_resolutions.find(&source.name) {
 2324                      None => {
 2325                          // The containing module definitely doesn't have an
 2326                          // exported import with the name in question. We can
 2327                          // therefore accurately report that the names are
 2328                          // unbound.
 2329  
 2330                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
 2331                              value_result = UnboundResult;
 2332                          }
 2333                          if type_result.is_unknown() {
 2334                              type_result = UnboundResult;
 2335                          }
 2336                      }
 2337                      Some(import_resolution)
 2338                              if import_resolution.outstanding_references
 2339                                  == 0 => {
 2340  
 2341                          fn get_binding(this: @mut Resolver,
 2342                                         import_resolution:
 2343                                            @mut ImportResolution,
 2344                                         namespace: Namespace)
 2345                                      -> NamespaceResult {
 2346  
 2347                              // Import resolutions must be declared with "pub"
 2348                              // in order to be exported.
 2349                              if import_resolution.privacy == Private {
 2350                                  return UnboundResult;
 2351                              }
 2352  
 2353                              match (*import_resolution).
 2354                                      target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 2355                                  None => {
 2356                                      return UnboundResult;
 2357                                  }
 2358                                  Some(target) => {
 2359                                      let id = import_resolution.id(namespace);
 2360                                      this.used_imports.insert(id);
 2361                                      return BoundResult(target.target_module,
 2362                                                         target.bindings);
 2363                                  }
 2364                              }
 2365                          }
 2366  
 2367                          // The name is an import which has been fully
 2368                          // resolved. We can, therefore, just follow it.
 2369                          if value_result.is_unknown() {
 2370                              value_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2371                                                         ValueNS);
 2372                          }
 2373                          if type_result.is_unknown() {
 2374                              type_result = get_binding(self, *import_resolution,
 2375                                                        TypeNS);
 2376                          }
 2377                      }
 2378                      Some(_) => {
 2379                          // The import is unresolved. Bail out.
 2380                          debug!("(resolving single import) unresolved import; \
 2381                                  bailing out");
 2382                          return Indeterminate;
 2383                      }
 2384                  }
 2385              }
 2386          }
 2387  
 2388          // If we didn't find a result in the type namespace, search the
 2389          // external modules.
 2390          match type_result {
 2391              BoundResult(*) => {}
 2392              _ => {
 2393                  match containing_module.external_module_children
 2394                                         .find(&source.name) {
 2395                      None => {} // Continue.
 2396                      Some(module) => {
 2397                          let name_bindings =
 2398                              @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(
 2399                                  *module);
 2400                          type_result = BoundResult(containing_module,
 2401                                                    name_bindings);
 2402                      }
 2403                  }
 2404              }
 2405          }
 2406  
 2407          // We've successfully resolved the import. Write the results in.
 2408          assert!(module_.import_resolutions.contains_key(&target.name));
 2409          let import_resolution = module_.import_resolutions.get(&target.name);
 2410  
 2411          match value_result {
 2412              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2413                  debug!("(resolving single import) found value target");
 2414                  import_resolution.value_target =
 2415                      Some(Target::new(target_module, name_bindings));
 2416                  import_resolution.value_id = directive.id;
 2417              }
 2418              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2419              UnknownResult => {
 2420                  fail!("value result should be known at this point");
 2421              }
 2422          }
 2423          match type_result {
 2424              BoundResult(target_module, name_bindings) => {
 2425                  debug!("(resolving single import) found type target: %?",
 2426                          name_bindings.type_def.unwrap().type_def);
 2427                  import_resolution.type_target =
 2428                      Some(Target::new(target_module, name_bindings));
 2429                  import_resolution.type_id = directive.id;
 2430              }
 2431              UnboundResult => { /* Continue. */ }
 2432              UnknownResult => {
 2433                  fail!("type result should be known at this point");
 2434              }
 2435          }
 2436  
 2437          let i = import_resolution;
 2438          let mut resolve_fail = false;
 2439          let mut priv_fail = false;
 2440          match (i.value_target, i.type_target) {
 2441              // If this name wasn't found in either namespace, it's definitely
 2442              // unresolved.
 2443              (None, None) => { resolve_fail = true; }
 2444              // If it's private, it's also unresolved.
 2445              (Some(t), None) | (None, Some(t)) => {
 2446                  let bindings = &mut *t.bindings;
 2447                  match bindings.type_def {
 2448                      Some(ref type_def) => {
 2449                          if type_def.privacy == Private {
 2450                              priv_fail = true;
 2451                          }
 2452                      }
 2453                      _ => ()
 2454                  }
 2455                  match bindings.value_def {
 2456                      Some(ref value_def) => {
 2457                          if value_def.privacy == Private {
 2458                              priv_fail = true;
 2459                          }
 2460                      }
 2461                      _ => ()
 2462                  }
 2463              }
 2464              // It's also an error if there's both a type and a value with this
 2465              // name, but both are private
 2466              (Some(val), Some(ty)) => {
 2467                  match (val.bindings.value_def, ty.bindings.value_def) {
 2468                      (Some(ref value_def), Some(ref type_def)) =>
 2469                          if value_def.privacy == Private
 2470                              && type_def.privacy == Private {
 2471                                  priv_fail = true;
 2472                          },
 2473                      _ => ()
 2474                  }
 2475              }
 2476          }
 2477  
 2478          let span = directive.span;
 2479          if resolve_fail {
 2480              self.resolve_error(span, fmt!("unresolved import: there is no `%s` in `%s`",
 2481                                               self.session.str_of(source),
 2482                                               self.module_to_str(containing_module)));
 2483              return Failed;
 2484          } else if priv_fail {
 2485              self.resolve_error(span, fmt!("unresolved import: found `%s` in `%s` but it is \
 2486                                               private", self.session.str_of(source),
 2487                                               self.module_to_str(containing_module)));
 2488              return Failed;
 2489          }
 2490  
 2491          assert!(import_resolution.outstanding_references >= 1);
 2492          import_resolution.outstanding_references -= 1;
 2493  
 2494          debug!("(resolving single import) successfully resolved import");
 2495          return Success(());
 2496      }
 2497  
 2498      // Resolves a glob import. Note that this function cannot fail; it either
 2499      // succeeds or bails out (as importing * from an empty module or a module
 2500      // that exports nothing is valid).
 2501      pub fn resolve_glob_import(@mut self,
 2502                                 privacy: Privacy,
 2503                                 module_: @mut Module,
 2504                                 containing_module: @mut Module,
 2505                                 id: NodeId)
 2506                                 -> ResolveResult<()> {
 2507          // This function works in a highly imperative manner; it eagerly adds
 2508          // everything it can to the list of import resolutions of the module
 2509          // node.
 2510          debug!("(resolving glob import) resolving %? glob import", privacy);
 2511  
 2512          // We must bail out if the node has unresolved imports of any kind
 2513          // (including globs).
 2514          if !(*containing_module).all_imports_resolved() {
 2515              debug!("(resolving glob import) target module has unresolved \
 2516                      imports; bailing out");
 2517              return Indeterminate;
 2518          }
 2519  
 2520          assert_eq!(containing_module.glob_count, 0);
 2521  
 2522          // Add all resolved imports from the containing module.
 2523          for (ident, target_import_resolution) in containing_module.import_resolutions.iter() {
 2524  
 2525              debug!("(resolving glob import) writing module resolution \
 2526                      %? into `%s`",
 2527                     target_import_resolution.type_target.is_none(),
 2528                     self.module_to_str(module_));
 2529  
 2530              // Here we merge two import resolutions.
 2531              match module_.import_resolutions.find(ident) {
 2532                  None if target_import_resolution.privacy == Public => {
 2533                      // Simple: just copy the old import resolution.
 2534                      let new_import_resolution =
 2535                          @mut ImportResolution::new(privacy, id);
 2536                      new_import_resolution.value_target =
 2537                          target_import_resolution.value_target;
 2538                      new_import_resolution.type_target =
 2539                          target_import_resolution.type_target;
 2540  
 2541                      module_.import_resolutions.insert
 2542                          (*ident, new_import_resolution);
 2543                  }
 2544                  None => { /* continue ... */ }
 2545                  Some(&dest_import_resolution) => {
 2546                      // Merge the two import resolutions at a finer-grained
 2547                      // level.
 2548  
 2549                      match target_import_resolution.value_target {
 2550                          None => {
 2551                              // Continue.
 2552                          }
 2553                          Some(value_target) => {
 2554                              dest_import_resolution.value_target =
 2555                                  Some(value_target);
 2556                          }
 2557                      }
 2558                      match target_import_resolution.type_target {
 2559                          None => {
 2560                              // Continue.
 2561                          }
 2562                          Some(type_target) => {
 2563                              dest_import_resolution.type_target =
 2564                                  Some(type_target);
 2565                          }
 2566                      }
 2567                  }
 2568              }
 2569          }
 2570  
 2571          let merge_import_resolution = |name,
 2572                                         name_bindings: @mut NameBindings| {
 2573              let dest_import_resolution;
 2574              match module_.import_resolutions.find(&name) {
 2575                  None => {
 2576                      // Create a new import resolution from this child.
 2577                      dest_import_resolution = @mut ImportResolution::new(privacy, id);
 2578                      module_.import_resolutions.insert
 2579                          (name, dest_import_resolution);
 2580                  }
 2581                  Some(&existing_import_resolution) => {
 2582                      dest_import_resolution = existing_import_resolution;
 2583                  }
 2584              }
 2585  
 2586              debug!("(resolving glob import) writing resolution `%s` in `%s` \
 2587                      to `%s`, privacy=%?",
 2588                     interner_get(name),
 2589                     self.module_to_str(containing_module),
 2590                     self.module_to_str(module_),
 2591                     dest_import_resolution.privacy);
 2592  
 2593              // Merge the child item into the import resolution.
 2594              if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(ValueNS) {
 2595                  debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for value target");
 2596                  dest_import_resolution.value_target =
 2597                      Some(Target::new(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2598                  dest_import_resolution.value_id = id;
 2599              }
 2600              if name_bindings.defined_in_public_namespace(TypeNS) {
 2601                  debug!("(resolving glob import) ... for type target");
 2602                  dest_import_resolution.type_target =
 2603                      Some(Target::new(containing_module, name_bindings));
 2604                  dest_import_resolution.type_id = id;
 2605              }
 2606          };
 2607  
 2608          // Add all children from the containing module.
 2609          self.populate_module_if_necessary(containing_module);
 2610          for (&name, name_bindings) in containing_module.children.iter() {
 2611              merge_import_resolution(name, *name_bindings);
 2612          }
 2613  
 2614          // Add external module children from the containing module.
 2615          for (&name, module) in containing_module.external_module_children.iter() {
 2616              let name_bindings =
 2617                  @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(*module);
 2618              merge_import_resolution(name, name_bindings);
 2619          }
 2620  
 2621          debug!("(resolving glob import) successfully resolved import");
 2622          return Success(());
 2623      }
 2624  
 2625      /// Resolves the given module path from the given root `module_`.
 2626      pub fn resolve_module_path_from_root(@mut self,
 2627                                           module_: @mut Module,
 2628                                           module_path: &[Ident],
 2629                                           index: uint,
 2630                                           span: Span,
 2631                                           mut name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 2632                                           -> ResolveResult<@mut Module> {
 2633          let mut search_module = module_;
 2634          let mut index = index;
 2635          let module_path_len = module_path.len();
 2636  
 2637          // Resolve the module part of the path. This does not involve looking
 2638          // upward though scope chains; we simply resolve names directly in
 2639          // modules as we go.
 2640          while index < module_path_len {
 2641              let name = module_path[index];
 2642              match self.resolve_name_in_module(search_module,
 2643                                                name,
 2644                                                TypeNS,
 2645                                                name_search_type) {
 2646                  Failed => {
 2647                      let segment_name = self.session.str_of(name);
 2648                      let module_name = self.module_to_str(search_module);
 2649                      if "???" == module_name {
 2650                          let span = Span {
 2651                              lo: span.lo,
 2652                              hi: span.lo + BytePos(segment_name.len()),
 2653                              expn_info: span.expn_info,
 2654                          };
 2655                          self.resolve_error(span,
 2656                                                fmt!("unresolved import. maybe \
 2657                                                      a missing `extern mod \
 2658                                                      %s`?",
 2659                                                      segment_name));
 2660                          return Failed;
 2661                      }
 2662                      self.resolve_error(span, fmt!("unresolved import: could not find `%s` in \
 2663                                                       `%s`.", segment_name, module_name));
 2664                      return Failed;
 2665                  }
 2666                  Indeterminate => {
 2667                      debug!("(resolving module path for import) module \
 2668                              resolution is indeterminate: %s",
 2669                              self.session.str_of(name));
 2670                      return Indeterminate;
 2671                  }
 2672                  Success(target) => {
 2673                      // Check to see whether there are type bindings, and, if
 2674                      // so, whether there is a module within.
 2675                      match target.bindings.type_def {
 2676                          Some(type_def) => {
 2677                              match type_def.module_def {
 2678                                  None => {
 2679                                      // Not a module.
 2680                                      self.resolve_error(span,
 2681                                                            fmt!("not a \
 2682                                                                  module `%s`",
 2683                                                                 self.session.
 2684                                                                     str_of(
 2685                                                                      name)));
 2686                                      return Failed;
 2687                                  }
 2688                                  Some(module_def) => {
 2689                                      // If we're doing the search for an
 2690                                      // import, do not allow traits and impls
 2691                                      // to be selected.
 2692                                      match (name_search_type,
 2693                                             module_def.kind) {
 2694                                          (ImportSearch, TraitModuleKind) |
 2695                                          (ImportSearch, ImplModuleKind) => {
 2696                                              self.resolve_error(
 2697                                                  span,
 2698                                                  "cannot import from a trait \
 2699                                                   or type implementation");
 2700                                              return Failed;
 2701                                          }
 2702                                          (_, _) => search_module = module_def,
 2703                                      }
 2704                                  }
 2705                              }
 2706                          }
 2707                          None => {
 2708                              // There are no type bindings at all.
 2709                              self.resolve_error(span,
 2710                                                    fmt!("not a module `%s`",
 2711                                                         self.session.str_of(
 2712                                                              name)));
 2713                              return Failed;
 2714                          }
 2715                      }
 2716                  }
 2717              }
 2718  
 2719              index += 1;
 2720  
 2721              // After the first element of the path, allow searching only
 2722              // through public identifiers.
 2723              //
 2724              // XXX: Rip this out and move it to the privacy checker.
 2725              if name_search_type == PathPublicOrPrivateSearch {
 2726                  name_search_type = PathPublicOnlySearch
 2727              }
 2728          }
 2729  
 2730          return Success(search_module);
 2731      }
 2732  
 2733      /// Attempts to resolve the module part of an import directive or path
 2734      /// rooted at the given module.
 2735      pub fn resolve_module_path(@mut self,
 2736                                 module_: @mut Module,
 2737                                 module_path: &[Ident],
 2738                                 use_lexical_scope: UseLexicalScopeFlag,
 2739                                 span: Span,
 2740                                 name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 2741                                 -> ResolveResult<@mut Module> {
 2742          let module_path_len = module_path.len();
 2743          assert!(module_path_len > 0);
 2744  
 2745          debug!("(resolving module path for import) processing `%s` rooted at \
 2746                 `%s`",
 2747                 self.idents_to_str(module_path),
 2748                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2749  
 2750          // Resolve the module prefix, if any.
 2751          let module_prefix_result = self.resolve_module_prefix(module_,
 2752                                                                module_path);
 2753  
 2754          let search_module;
 2755          let start_index;
 2756          match module_prefix_result {
 2757              Failed => {
 2758                  let mpath = self.idents_to_str(module_path);
 2759                  match mpath.rfind(':') {
 2760                      Some(idx) => {
 2761                          self.resolve_error(span, fmt!("unresolved import: could not find `%s` \
 2762                                                           in `%s`",
 2763                                                           // idx +- 1 to account for the colons
 2764                                                           // on either side
 2765                                                           mpath.slice_from(idx + 1),
 2766                                                           mpath.slice_to(idx - 1)));
 2767                      },
 2768                      None => (),
 2769                  };
 2770                  return Failed;
 2771              }
 2772              Indeterminate => {
 2773                  debug!("(resolving module path for import) indeterminate; \
 2774                          bailing");
 2775                  return Indeterminate;
 2776              }
 2777              Success(NoPrefixFound) => {
 2778                  // There was no prefix, so we're considering the first element
 2779                  // of the path. How we handle this depends on whether we were
 2780                  // instructed to use lexical scope or not.
 2781                  match use_lexical_scope {
 2782                      DontUseLexicalScope => {
 2783                          // This is a crate-relative path. We will start the
 2784                          // resolution process at index zero.
 2785                          search_module = self.graph_root.get_module();
 2786                          start_index = 0;
 2787                      }
 2788                      UseLexicalScope => {
 2789                          // This is not a crate-relative path. We resolve the
 2790                          // first component of the path in the current lexical
 2791                          // scope and then proceed to resolve below that.
 2792                          let result = self.resolve_module_in_lexical_scope(
 2793                              module_,
 2794                              module_path[0]);
 2795                          match result {
 2796                              Failed => {
 2797                                  self.resolve_error(span, "unresolved name");
 2798                                  return Failed;
 2799                              }
 2800                              Indeterminate => {
 2801                                  debug!("(resolving module path for import) \
 2802                                          indeterminate; bailing");
 2803                                  return Indeterminate;
 2804                              }
 2805                              Success(containing_module) => {
 2806                                  search_module = containing_module;
 2807                                  start_index = 1;
 2808                              }
 2809                          }
 2810                      }
 2811                  }
 2812              }
 2813              Success(PrefixFound(containing_module, index)) => {
 2814                  search_module = containing_module;
 2815                  start_index = index;
 2816              }
 2817          }
 2818  
 2819          self.resolve_module_path_from_root(search_module,
 2820                                             module_path,
 2821                                             start_index,
 2822                                             span,
 2823                                             name_search_type)
 2824      }
 2825  
 2826      /// Invariant: This must only be called during main resolution, not during
 2827      /// import resolution.
 2828      pub fn resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(@mut self,
 2829                                           module_: @mut Module,
 2830                                           name: Ident,
 2831                                           namespace: Namespace,
 2832                                           search_through_modules:
 2833                                           SearchThroughModulesFlag)
 2834                                           -> ResolveResult<Target> {
 2835          debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) resolving `%s` in \
 2836                  namespace %? in `%s`",
 2837                 self.session.str_of(name),
 2838                 namespace,
 2839                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 2840  
 2841          // The current module node is handled specially. First, check for
 2842          // its immediate children.
 2843          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 2844          match module_.children.find(&name.name) {
 2845              Some(name_bindings)
 2846                      if name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(namespace) => {
 2847                  return Success(Target::new(module_, *name_bindings));
 2848              }
 2849              Some(_) | None => { /* Not found; continue. */ }
 2850          }
 2851  
 2852          // Now check for its import directives. We don't have to have resolved
 2853          // all its imports in the usual way; this is because chains of
 2854          // adjacent import statements are processed as though they mutated the
 2855          // current scope.
 2856          match module_.import_resolutions.find(&name.name) {
 2857              None => {
 2858                  // Not found; continue.
 2859              }
 2860              Some(import_resolution) => {
 2861                  match (*import_resolution).target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 2862                      None => {
 2863                          // Not found; continue.
 2864                          debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) found \
 2865                                  import resolution, but not in namespace %?",
 2866                                 namespace);
 2867                      }
 2868                      Some(target) => {
 2869                          debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) using \
 2870                                  import resolution");
 2871                          self.used_imports.insert(import_resolution.id(namespace));
 2872                          return Success(target);
 2873                      }
 2874                  }
 2875              }
 2876          }
 2877  
 2878          // Search for external modules.
 2879          if namespace == TypeNS {
 2880              match module_.external_module_children.find(&name.name) {
 2881                  None => {}
 2882                  Some(module) => {
 2883                      let name_bindings =
 2884                          @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(
 2885                              *module);
 2886                      return Success(Target::new(module_, name_bindings));
 2887                  }
 2888              }
 2889          }
 2890  
 2891          // Finally, proceed up the scope chain looking for parent modules.
 2892          let mut search_module = module_;
 2893          loop {
 2894              // Go to the next parent.
 2895              match search_module.parent_link {
 2896                  NoParentLink => {
 2897                      // No more parents. This module was unresolved.
 2898                      debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) unresolved \
 2899                              module");
 2900                      return Failed;
 2901                  }
 2902                  ModuleParentLink(parent_module_node, _) => {
 2903                      match search_through_modules {
 2904                          DontSearchThroughModules => {
 2905                              match search_module.kind {
 2906                                  NormalModuleKind => {
 2907                                      // We stop the search here.
 2908                                      debug!("(resolving item in lexical \
 2909                                              scope) unresolved module: not \
 2910                                              searching through module \
 2911                                              parents");
 2912                                      return Failed;
 2913                                  }
 2914                                  ExternModuleKind |
 2915                                  TraitModuleKind |
 2916                                  ImplModuleKind |
 2917                                  AnonymousModuleKind => {
 2918                                      search_module = parent_module_node;
 2919                                  }
 2920                              }
 2921                          }
 2922                          SearchThroughModules => {
 2923                              search_module = parent_module_node;
 2924                          }
 2925                      }
 2926                  }
 2927                  BlockParentLink(parent_module_node, _) => {
 2928                      search_module = parent_module_node;
 2929                  }
 2930              }
 2931  
 2932              // Resolve the name in the parent module.
 2933              match self.resolve_name_in_module(search_module,
 2934                                                name,
 2935                                                namespace,
 2936                                                PathPublicOrPrivateSearch) {
 2937                  Failed => {
 2938                      // Continue up the search chain.
 2939                  }
 2940                  Indeterminate => {
 2941                      // We couldn't see through the higher scope because of an
 2942                      // unresolved import higher up. Bail.
 2943  
 2944                      debug!("(resolving item in lexical scope) indeterminate \
 2945                              higher scope; bailing");
 2946                      return Indeterminate;
 2947                  }
 2948                  Success(target) => {
 2949                      // We found the module.
 2950                      return Success(target);
 2951                  }
 2952              }
 2953          }
 2954      }
 2955  
 2956      /// Resolves a module name in the current lexical scope.
 2957      pub fn resolve_module_in_lexical_scope(@mut self,
 2958                                             module_: @mut Module,
 2959                                             name: Ident)
 2960                                             -> ResolveResult<@mut Module> {
 2961          // If this module is an anonymous module, resolve the item in the
 2962          // lexical scope. Otherwise, resolve the item from the crate root.
 2963          let resolve_result = self.resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(
 2964              module_, name, TypeNS, DontSearchThroughModules);
 2965          match resolve_result {
 2966              Success(target) => {
 2967                  let bindings = &mut *target.bindings;
 2968                  match bindings.type_def {
 2969                      Some(ref type_def) => {
 2970                          match (*type_def).module_def {
 2971                              None => {
 2972                                  error!("!!! (resolving module in lexical \
 2973                                          scope) module wasn't actually a \
 2974                                          module!");
 2975                                  return Failed;
 2976                              }
 2977                              Some(module_def) => {
 2978                                  return Success(module_def);
 2979                              }
 2980                          }
 2981                      }
 2982                      None => {
 2983                          error!("!!! (resolving module in lexical scope) module
 2984                                  wasn't actually a module!");
 2985                          return Failed;
 2986                      }
 2987                  }
 2988              }
 2989              Indeterminate => {
 2990                  debug!("(resolving module in lexical scope) indeterminate; \
 2991                          bailing");
 2992                  return Indeterminate;
 2993              }
 2994              Failed => {
 2995                  debug!("(resolving module in lexical scope) failed to \
 2996                          resolve");
 2997                  return Failed;
 2998              }
 2999          }
 3000      }

 3002      /// Returns the nearest normal module parent of the given module.
 3003      pub fn get_nearest_normal_module_parent(@mut self, module_: @mut Module)
 3004                                              -> Option<@mut Module> {
 3005          let mut module_ = module_;
 3006          loop {
 3007              match module_.parent_link {
 3008                  NoParentLink => return None,
 3009                  ModuleParentLink(new_module, _) |
 3010                  BlockParentLink(new_module, _) => {
 3011                      match new_module.kind {
 3012                          NormalModuleKind => return Some(new_module),
 3013                          ExternModuleKind |
 3014                          TraitModuleKind |
 3015                          ImplModuleKind |
 3016                          AnonymousModuleKind => module_ = new_module,
 3017                      }
 3018                  }
 3019              }
 3020          }
 3021      }
 3022  
 3023      /// Returns the nearest normal module parent of the given module, or the
 3024      /// module itself if it is a normal module.
 3025      pub fn get_nearest_normal_module_parent_or_self(@mut self,
 3026                                                      module_: @mut Module)
 3027                                                      -> @mut Module {
 3028          match module_.kind {
 3029              NormalModuleKind => return module_,
 3030              ExternModuleKind |
 3031              TraitModuleKind |
 3032              ImplModuleKind |
 3033              AnonymousModuleKind => {
 3034                  match self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent(module_) {
 3035                      None => module_,
 3036                      Some(new_module) => new_module
 3037                  }
 3038              }
 3039          }
 3040      }
 3041  
 3042      /// Resolves a "module prefix". A module prefix is one or both of (a) `self::`;
 3043      /// (b) some chain of `super::`.
 3044      /// grammar: (SELF MOD_SEP ) ? (SUPER MOD_SEP) *
 3045      pub fn resolve_module_prefix(@mut self,
 3046                                   module_: @mut Module,
 3047                                   module_path: &[Ident])
 3048                                   -> ResolveResult<ModulePrefixResult> {
 3049          // Start at the current module if we see `self` or `super`, or at the
 3050          // top of the crate otherwise.
 3051          let mut containing_module;
 3052          let mut i;
 3053          if "self" == token::ident_to_str(&module_path[0]) {
 3054              containing_module =
 3055                  self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent_or_self(module_);
 3056              i = 1;
 3057          } else if "super" == token::ident_to_str(&module_path[0]) {
 3058              containing_module =
 3059                  self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent_or_self(module_);
 3060              i = 0;  // We'll handle `super` below.
 3061          } else {
 3062              return Success(NoPrefixFound);
 3063          }
 3064  
 3065          // Now loop through all the `super`s we find.
 3066          while i < module_path.len() &&
 3067                  "super" == token::ident_to_str(&module_path[i]) {
 3068              debug!("(resolving module prefix) resolving `super` at %s",
 3069                     self.module_to_str(containing_module));
 3070              match self.get_nearest_normal_module_parent(containing_module) {
 3071                  None => return Failed,
 3072                  Some(new_module) => {
 3073                      containing_module = new_module;
 3074                      i += 1;
 3075                  }
 3076              }
 3077          }
 3078  
 3079          debug!("(resolving module prefix) finished resolving prefix at %s",
 3080                 self.module_to_str(containing_module));
 3081  
 3082          return Success(PrefixFound(containing_module, i));
 3083      }
 3084  
 3085      /// Attempts to resolve the supplied name in the given module for the
 3086      /// given namespace. If successful, returns the target corresponding to
 3087      /// the name.
 3088      pub fn resolve_name_in_module(@mut self,
 3089                                    module_: @mut Module,
 3090                                    name: Ident,
 3091                                    namespace: Namespace,
 3092                                    name_search_type: NameSearchType)
 3093                                    -> ResolveResult<Target> {
 3094          debug!("(resolving name in module) resolving `%s` in `%s`",
 3095                 self.session.str_of(name),
 3096                 self.module_to_str(module_));
 3097  
 3098          // First, check the direct children of the module.
 3099          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 3100          match module_.children.find(&name.name) {
 3101              Some(name_bindings)
 3102                      if name_bindings.defined_in_namespace(namespace) => {
 3103                  debug!("(resolving name in module) found node as child");
 3104                  return Success(Target::new(module_, *name_bindings));
 3105              }
 3106              Some(_) | None => {
 3107                  // Continue.
 3108              }
 3109          }
 3110  
 3111          // Next, check the module's imports if necessary.
 3112  
 3113          // If this is a search of all imports, we should be done with glob
 3114          // resolution at this point.
 3115          if name_search_type == PathPublicOrPrivateSearch ||
 3116                  name_search_type == PathPublicOnlySearch {
 3117              assert_eq!(module_.glob_count, 0);
 3118          }
 3119  
 3120          // Check the list of resolved imports.
 3121          match module_.import_resolutions.find(&name.name) {
 3122              Some(import_resolution) => {
 3123                  if import_resolution.privacy == Public &&
 3124                          import_resolution.outstanding_references != 0 {
 3125                      debug!("(resolving name in module) import \
 3126                              unresolved; bailing out");
 3127                      return Indeterminate;
 3128                  }
 3129  
 3130                  match import_resolution.target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 3131                      None => {
 3132                          debug!("(resolving name in module) name found, \
 3133                                  but not in namespace %?",
 3134                                 namespace);
 3135                      }
 3136                      Some(target)
 3137                              if name_search_type ==
 3138                                  PathPublicOrPrivateSearch ||
 3139                              import_resolution.privacy == Public => {
 3140                          debug!("(resolving name in module) resolved to \
 3141                                  import");
 3142                          self.used_imports.insert(import_resolution.id(namespace));
 3143                          return Success(target);
 3144                      }
 3145                      Some(_) => {
 3146                          debug!("(resolving name in module) name found, \
 3147                                  but not public");
 3148                      }
 3149                  }
 3150              }
 3151              None => {} // Continue.
 3152          }
 3153  
 3154          // Finally, search through external children.
 3155          if namespace == TypeNS {
 3156              match module_.external_module_children.find(&name.name) {
 3157                  None => {}
 3158                  Some(module) => {
 3159                      let name_bindings =
 3160                          @mut Resolver::create_name_bindings_from_module(
 3161                              *module);
 3162                      return Success(Target::new(module_, name_bindings));
 3163                  }
 3164              }
 3165          }
 3166  
 3167          // We're out of luck.
 3168          debug!("(resolving name in module) failed to resolve `%s`",
 3169                 self.session.str_of(name));
 3170          return Failed;
 3171      }

 3173      pub fn report_unresolved_imports(@mut self, module_: @mut Module) {
 3174          let index = module_.resolved_import_count;
 3175          let imports: &mut ~[@ImportDirective] = &mut *module_.imports;
 3176          let import_count = imports.len();
 3177          if index != import_count {
 3178              let sn = self.session.codemap.span_to_snippet(imports[index].span).unwrap();
 3179              if sn.contains("::") {
 3180                  self.resolve_error(imports[index].span, "unresolved import");
 3181              } else {
 3182                  let err = fmt!("unresolved import (maybe you meant `%s::*`?)",
 3183                                 sn.slice(0, sn.len()));
 3184                  self.resolve_error(imports[index].span, err);
 3185              }
 3186          }
 3187  
 3188          // Descend into children and anonymous children.
 3189          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 3190          for (_, &child_node) in module_.children.iter() {
 3191              match child_node.get_module_if_available() {
 3192                  None => {
 3193                      // Continue.
 3194                  }
 3195                  Some(child_module) => {
 3196                      self.report_unresolved_imports(child_module);
 3197                  }
 3198              }
 3199          }
 3200  
 3201          for (_, &module_) in module_.anonymous_children.iter() {
 3202              self.report_unresolved_imports(module_);
 3203          }
 3204      }

 3220      pub fn record_exports_for_module_subtree(@mut self,
 3221                                               module_: @mut Module) {
 3222          // If this isn't a local crate, then bail out. We don't need to record
 3223          // exports for nonlocal crates.
 3224  
 3225          match module_.def_id {
 3226              Some(def_id) if def_id.crate == LOCAL_CRATE => {
 3227                  // OK. Continue.
 3228                  debug!("(recording exports for module subtree) recording \
 3229                          exports for local module `%s`",
 3230                         self.module_to_str(module_));
 3231              }
 3232              None => {
 3233                  // Record exports for the root module.
 3234                  debug!("(recording exports for module subtree) recording \
 3235                          exports for root module `%s`",
 3236                         self.module_to_str(module_));
 3237              }
 3238              Some(_) => {
 3239                  // Bail out.
 3240                  debug!("(recording exports for module subtree) not recording \
 3241                          exports for `%s`",
 3242                         self.module_to_str(module_));
 3243                  return;
 3244              }
 3245          }
 3246  
 3247          self.record_exports_for_module(module_);
 3248          self.populate_module_if_necessary(module_);
 3249  
 3250          for (_, &child_name_bindings) in module_.children.iter() {
 3251              match child_name_bindings.get_module_if_available() {
 3252                  None => {
 3253                      // Nothing to do.
 3254                  }
 3255                  Some(child_module) => {
 3256                      self.record_exports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 3257                  }
 3258              }
 3259          }
 3260  
 3261          for (_, &child_module) in module_.anonymous_children.iter() {
 3262              self.record_exports_for_module_subtree(child_module);
 3263          }
 3264      }
 3265  
 3266      pub fn record_exports_for_module(@mut self, module_: @mut Module) {
 3267          let mut exports2 = ~[];

 3275              }

 3277          }
 3278      }

 3280      pub fn add_exports_of_namebindings(@mut self,
 3281                                         exports2: &mut ~[Export2],
 3282                                         name: Name,
 3283                                         namebindings: @mut NameBindings,
 3284                                         ns: Namespace,
 3285                                         reexport: bool) {
 3286          match (namebindings.def_for_namespace(ns),
 3287                 namebindings.privacy_for_namespace(ns)) {
 3288              (Some(d), Some(Public)) => {

 3290                         if reexport { ~"reexport" } else { ~"export"},
 3291                         interner_get(name),
 3292                         def_id_of_def(d));
 3293                  exports2.push(Export2 {
 3294                      reexport: reexport,
 3295                      name: interner_get(name),
 3296                      def_id: def_id_of_def(d)
 3297                  });
 3298              }
 3299              (Some(_), Some(privacy)) => {
 3300                  debug!("(computing reexports) NO: privacy %?", privacy);
 3301              }
 3302              (d_opt, p_opt) => {
 3303                  debug!("(computing reexports) NO: %?, %?", d_opt, p_opt);
 3304              }
 3305          }
 3306      }
 3307  
 3308      pub fn add_exports_for_module(@mut self,
 3309                                    exports2: &mut ~[Export2],
 3310                                    module_: @mut Module) {
 3311          for (name, importresolution) in module_.import_resolutions.iter() {
 3312              if importresolution.privacy != Public {
 3313                  debug!("(computing exports) not reexporting private `%s`",
 3314                         interner_get(*name));
 3315                  loop;
 3316              }
 3317              let xs = [TypeNS, ValueNS];
 3318              for ns in xs.iter() {
 3319                  match importresolution.target_for_namespace(*ns) {
 3320                      Some(target) => {
 3321                          debug!("(computing exports) maybe reexport '%s'",
 3322                                 interner_get(*name));
 3323                          self.add_exports_of_namebindings(&mut *exports2,
 3324                                                           *name,
 3325                                                           target.bindings,
 3326                                                           *ns,
 3327                                                           true)
 3328                      }
 3329                      _ => ()
 3330                  }
 3331              }
 3332          }
 3333      }
 3334  
 3335      // AST resolution
 3336      //
 3337      // We maintain a list of value ribs and type ribs.
 3338      //
 3339      // Simultaneously, we keep track of the current position in the module
 3340      // graph in the `current_module` pointer. When we go to resolve a name in
 3341      // the value or type namespaces, we first look through all the ribs and
 3342      // then query the module graph. When we resolve a name in the module
 3343      // namespace, we can skip all the ribs (since nested modules are not
 3344      // allowed within blocks in Rust) and jump straight to the current module
 3345      // graph node.
 3346      //
 3347      // Named implementations are handled separately. When we find a method
 3348      // call, we consult the module node to find all of the implementations in
 3349      // scope. This information is lazily cached in the module node. We then
 3350      // generate a fake "implementation scope" containing all the
 3351      // implementations thus found, for compatibility with old resolve pass.
 3352  
 3353      pub fn with_scope(@mut self, name: Option<Ident>, f: &fn()) {
 3354          let orig_module = self.current_module;
 3355  
 3356          // Move down in the graph.
 3357          match name {
 3358              None => {
 3359                  // Nothing to do.
 3360              }
 3361              Some(name) => {
 3362                  self.populate_module_if_necessary(orig_module);
 3363                  match orig_module.children.find(&name.name) {
 3364                      None => {
 3365                          debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find `%s` in `%s`",
 3366                                 self.session.str_of(name),
 3367                                 self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3368                      }
 3369                      Some(name_bindings) => {
 3370                          match (*name_bindings).get_module_if_available() {
 3371                              None => {
 3372                                  debug!("!!! (with scope) didn't find module \
 3373                                          for `%s` in `%s`",
 3374                                         self.session.str_of(name),
 3375                                         self.module_to_str(orig_module));
 3376                              }
 3377                              Some(module_) => {
 3378                                  self.current_module = module_;
 3379                              }
 3380                          }
 3381                      }
 3382                  }
 3383              }
 3384          }
 3385  
 3386          f();
 3387  
 3388          self.current_module = orig_module;
 3389      }
 3390  
 3391      /// Wraps the given definition in the appropriate number of `def_upvar`
 3392      /// wrappers.
 3393      pub fn upvarify(@mut self,
 3394                      ribs: &mut ~[@Rib],
 3395                      rib_index: uint,
 3396                      def_like: DefLike,
 3397                      span: Span,
 3398                      allow_capturing_self: AllowCapturingSelfFlag)
 3399                      -> Option<DefLike> {
 3400          let mut def;
 3401          let is_ty_param;
 3402  
 3403          match def_like {
 3404              DlDef(d @ DefLocal(*)) | DlDef(d @ DefUpvar(*)) |
 3405              DlDef(d @ DefArg(*)) | DlDef(d @ DefBinding(*)) => {
 3406                  def = d;
 3407                  is_ty_param = false;
 3408              }
 3409              DlDef(d @ DefTyParam(*)) => {
 3410                  def = d;
 3411                  is_ty_param = true;
 3412              }
 3413              DlDef(d @ DefSelf(*))
 3414                      if allow_capturing_self == DontAllowCapturingSelf => {
 3415                  def = d;
 3416                  is_ty_param = false;
 3417              }
 3418              _ => {
 3419                  return Some(def_like);
 3420              }
 3421          }
 3422  
 3423          let mut rib_index = rib_index + 1;
 3424          while rib_index < ribs.len() {
 3425              match ribs[rib_index].kind {
 3426                  NormalRibKind => {
 3427                      // Nothing to do. Continue.
 3428                  }
 3429                  FunctionRibKind(function_id, body_id) => {
 3430                      if !is_ty_param {
 3431                          def = DefUpvar(def_id_of_def(def).node,
 3432                                          @def,
 3433                                          function_id,
 3434                                          body_id);
 3435                      }
 3436                  }
 3437                  MethodRibKind(item_id, _) => {
 3438                    // If the def is a ty param, and came from the parent
 3439                    // item, it's ok
 3440                    match def {
 3441                      DefTyParam(did, _)
 3442                          if self.def_map.find(&did.node).map_move(|x| *x)
 3443                              == Some(DefTyParamBinder(item_id)) => {
 3444                        // ok
 3445                      }
 3446                      _ => {
 3447                      if !is_ty_param {
 3448                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3449                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3450                          // report an error.
 3451  
 3452                          self.resolve_error(
 3453                              span,
 3454                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3455                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3456                      } else {
 3457                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3458                          // its scope.
 3459  
 3460                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3461                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3462                                                argument out of scope");
 3463                      }
 3464  
 3465                      return None;
 3466                      }
 3467                    }
 3468                  }
 3469                  OpaqueFunctionRibKind => {
 3470                      if !is_ty_param {
 3471                          // This was an attempt to access an upvar inside a
 3472                          // named function item. This is not allowed, so we
 3473                          // report an error.
 3474  
 3475                          self.resolve_error(
 3476                              span,
 3477                              "can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item; \
 3478                              use the || { ... } closure form instead");
 3479                      } else {
 3480                          // This was an attempt to use a type parameter outside
 3481                          // its scope.
 3482  
 3483                          self.resolve_error(span,
 3484                                                "attempt to use a type \
 3485                                                argument out of scope");
 3486                      }
 3487  
 3488                      return None;
 3489                  }
 3490                  ConstantItemRibKind => {
 3491                      // Still doesn't deal with upvars
 3492                      self.resolve_error(span,
 3493                                            "attempt to use a non-constant \
 3494                                             value in a constant");
 3495  
 3496                  }
 3497              }
 3498  
 3499              rib_index += 1;
 3500          }
 3501  
 3502          return Some(DlDef(def));
 3503      }
 3504  
 3505      pub fn search_ribs(@mut self,
 3506                         ribs: &mut ~[@Rib],
 3507                         name: Name,
 3508                         span: Span,
 3509                         allow_capturing_self: AllowCapturingSelfFlag)
 3510                         -> Option<DefLike> {
 3511          // FIXME #4950: This should not use a while loop.
 3512          // FIXME #4950: Try caching?
 3513  
 3514          let mut i = ribs.len();
 3515          while i != 0 {
 3516              i -= 1;
 3517              match ribs[i].bindings.find(&name) {
 3518                  Some(&def_like) => {
 3519                      return self.upvarify(ribs, i, def_like, span,
 3520                                           allow_capturing_self);
 3521                  }
 3522                  None => {
 3523                      // Continue.
 3524                  }
 3525              }
 3526          }
 3527  
 3528          return None;
 3529      }
