 3538      pub fn resolve_item(@mut self, item: @item, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 3539          debug!("(resolving item) resolving %s",
 3540                 self.session.str_of(item.ident));
 3541  
 3542          // Items with the !resolve_unexported attribute are X-ray contexts.
 3543          // This is used to allow the test runner to run unexported tests.
 3544          let orig_xray_flag = self.xray_context;
 3545          if attr::contains_name(item.attrs, "!resolve_unexported") {
 3546              self.xray_context = Xray;
 3547          }
 3548  
 3549          match item.node {
 3550  
 3551              // enum item: resolve all the variants' discrs,
 3552              // then resolve the ty params
 3553              item_enum(ref enum_def, ref generics) => {
 3554                  for variant in (*enum_def).variants.iter() {
 3555                      for dis_expr in variant.node.disr_expr.iter() {
 3556                          // resolve the discriminator expr
 3557                          // as a constant
 3558                          self.with_constant_rib(|| {
 3559                              self.resolve_expr(*dis_expr, visitor);
 3560                          });
 3561                      }
 3562                  }
 3563  
 3564                  // n.b. the discr expr gets visted twice.
 3565                  // but maybe it's okay since the first time will signal an
 3566                  // error if there is one? -- tjc
 3567                  do self.with_type_parameter_rib(
 3568                      HasTypeParameters(
 3569                          generics, item.id, 0, NormalRibKind)) {
 3570                      visit::walk_item(visitor, item, ());
 3571                  }
 3572              }
 3573  
 3574              item_ty(_, ref generics) => {
 3575                  do self.with_type_parameter_rib
 3576                          (HasTypeParameters(generics, item.id, 0,
 3577                                             NormalRibKind))
 3578                          || {
 3579  
 3580                      visit::walk_item(visitor, item, ());
 3581                  }
 3582              }
 3583  
 3584              item_impl(ref generics,
 3585                        ref implemented_traits,
 3586                        ref self_type,
 3587                        ref methods) => {
 3588                  self.resolve_implementation(item.id,
 3589                                              generics,
 3590                                              implemented_traits,
 3591                                              self_type,
 3592                                              *methods,
 3593                                              visitor);
 3594              }
 3595  
 3596              item_trait(ref generics, ref traits, ref methods) => {
 3597                  // Create a new rib for the self type.
 3598                  let self_type_rib = @Rib::new(NormalRibKind);
 3599                  self.type_ribs.push(self_type_rib);
 3600                  // plain insert (no renaming)
 3601                  let name = self.type_self_ident.name;
 3602                  self_type_rib.bindings.insert(name,
 3603                                                DlDef(DefSelfTy(item.id)));
 3604  
 3605                  // Create a new rib for the trait-wide type parameters.
 3606                  do self.with_type_parameter_rib
 3607                          (HasTypeParameters(generics, item.id, 0,
 3608                                             NormalRibKind)) {
 3609  
 3610                      self.resolve_type_parameters(&generics.ty_params,
 3611                                                   visitor);
 3612  
 3613                      // Resolve derived traits.
 3614                      for trt in traits.iter() {
 3615                          self.resolve_trait_reference(item.id, trt, visitor, TraitDerivation);
 3616                      }
 3617  
 3618                      for method in (*methods).iter() {
 3619                          // Create a new rib for the method-specific type
 3620                          // parameters.
 3621                          //
 3622                          // FIXME #4951: Do we need a node ID here?
 3623  
 3624                          match *method {
 3625                            required(ref ty_m) => {
 3626                              do self.with_type_parameter_rib
 3627                                  (HasTypeParameters(&ty_m.generics,
 3628                                                     item.id,
 3629                                                     generics.ty_params.len(),
 3630                                          MethodRibKind(item.id, Required))) {
 3631  
 3632                                  // Resolve the method-specific type
 3633                                  // parameters.
 3634                                  self.resolve_type_parameters(
 3635                                      &ty_m.generics.ty_params,
 3636                                      visitor);
 3637  
 3638                                  for argument in ty_m.decl.inputs.iter() {
 3639                                      self.resolve_type(&argument.ty, visitor);
 3640                                  }
 3641  
 3642                                  self.resolve_type(&ty_m.decl.output, visitor);
 3643                              }
 3644                            }
 3645                            provided(m) => {
 3646                                self.resolve_method(MethodRibKind(item.id,
 3647                                                       Provided(m.id)),
 3648                                                    m,
 3649                                                    generics.ty_params.len(),
 3650                                                    visitor)
 3651                            }
 3652                          }
 3653                      }
 3654                  }
 3655  
 3656                  self.type_ribs.pop();
 3657              }
 3658  
 3659              item_struct(ref struct_def, ref generics) => {
 3660                  self.resolve_struct(item.id,
 3661                                      generics,
 3662                                      struct_def.fields,
 3663                                      visitor);
 3664              }
 3665  
 3666              item_mod(ref module_) => {

 3669                                          item.id, visitor);
 3670                  }
 3671              }
 3672  
 3673              item_foreign_mod(ref foreign_module) => {

 3676                          match foreign_item.node {
 3677                              foreign_item_fn(_, ref generics) => {

 3680                                          generics, foreign_item.id, 0,

 3682                                      || visit::walk_foreign_item(visitor,
 3683                                                                  *foreign_item,
 3684                                                                  ()));
 3685                              }
 3686                              foreign_item_static(*) => {
 3687                                  visit::walk_foreign_item(visitor,
 3688                                                           *foreign_item,
 3689                                                           ());
 3690                              }
 3691                          }
 3692                      }
 3693                  }
 3694              }
 3695  
 3696              item_fn(ref fn_decl, _, _, ref generics, ref block) => {
 3697                  self.resolve_function(OpaqueFunctionRibKind,
 3698                                        Some(fn_decl),
 3699                                        HasTypeParameters
 3700                                          (generics,
 3701                                           item.id,
 3702                                           0,
 3703                                           OpaqueFunctionRibKind),

 3705                                        NoSelfBinding,
 3706                                        visitor);

 3708  
 3709              item_static(*) => {
 3710                  self.with_constant_rib(|| {
 3711                      visit::walk_item(visitor, item, ());
 3712                  });
 3713              }
 3714  
 3715            item_mac(*) => {
 3716              fail!("item macros unimplemented")
 3717            }
 3718          }
 3719  
 3720          self.xray_context = orig_xray_flag;
 3721      }
 3722  
 3723      pub fn with_type_parameter_rib(@mut self,
 3724                                     type_parameters: TypeParameters,
 3725                                     f: &fn()) {
 3726          match type_parameters {
 3727              HasTypeParameters(generics, node_id, initial_index,
 3728                                rib_kind) => {
 3729  
 3730                  let function_type_rib = @Rib::new(rib_kind);
 3731                  self.type_ribs.push(function_type_rib);
 3732  
 3733                  for (index, type_parameter) in generics.ty_params.iter().enumerate() {
 3734                      let ident = type_parameter.ident;
 3735                      debug!("with_type_parameter_rib: %d %d", node_id,
 3736                             type_parameter.id);
 3737                      let def_like = DlDef(DefTyParam
 3738                          (local_def(type_parameter.id),
 3739                           index + initial_index));
 3740                      // Associate this type parameter with
 3741                      // the item that bound it
 3742                      self.record_def(type_parameter.id,
 3743                                      DefTyParamBinder(node_id));
 3744                      // plain insert (no renaming)
 3745                      function_type_rib.bindings.insert(ident.name, def_like);
 3746                  }
 3747              }
 3748  
 3749              NoTypeParameters => {
 3750                  // Nothing to do.
 3751              }
 3752          }
 3753  
 3754          f();
 3755  
 3756          match type_parameters {
 3757              HasTypeParameters(*) => {
 3758                  self.type_ribs.pop();
 3759              }
 3760  
 3761              NoTypeParameters => {
 3762                  // Nothing to do.
 3763              }
 3764          }
 3765      }

 3768          self.label_ribs.push(@Rib::new(NormalRibKind));
 3769          f();
 3770          self.label_ribs.pop();
 3771      }

 3779      pub fn resolve_function(@mut self,
 3780                              rib_kind: RibKind,
 3781                              optional_declaration: Option<&fn_decl>,
 3782                              type_parameters: TypeParameters,
 3783                              block: &Block,
 3784                              self_binding: SelfBinding,
 3785                              visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 3786          // Create a value rib for the function.
 3787          let function_value_rib = @Rib::new(rib_kind);
 3788          self.value_ribs.push(function_value_rib);
 3789  
 3790          // Create a label rib for the function.
 3791          let function_label_rib = @Rib::new(rib_kind);
 3792          self.label_ribs.push(function_label_rib);
 3793  
 3794          // If this function has type parameters, add them now.
 3795          do self.with_type_parameter_rib(type_parameters) {
 3796              // Resolve the type parameters.
 3797              match type_parameters {
 3798                  NoTypeParameters => {
 3799                      // Continue.
 3800                  }
 3801                  HasTypeParameters(ref generics, _, _, _) => {
 3802                      self.resolve_type_parameters(&generics.ty_params,
 3803                                                   visitor);
 3804                  }
 3805              }
 3806  
 3807              // Add self to the rib, if necessary.
 3808              match self_binding {
 3809                  NoSelfBinding => {
 3810                      // Nothing to do.
 3811                  }
 3812                  HasSelfBinding(self_node_id) => {
 3813                      let def_like = DlDef(DefSelf(self_node_id));
 3814                      *function_value_rib.self_binding = Some(def_like);
 3815                  }
 3816              }
 3817  
 3818              // Add each argument to the rib.
 3819              match optional_declaration {
 3820                  None => {
 3821                      // Nothing to do.
 3822                  }
 3823                  Some(declaration) => {
 3824                      for argument in declaration.inputs.iter() {
 3825                          let binding_mode = ArgumentIrrefutableMode;
 3826                          let mutability =
 3827                              if argument.is_mutbl {Mutable} else {Immutable};
 3828                          self.resolve_pattern(argument.pat,
 3829                                               binding_mode,
 3830                                               mutability,
 3831                                               None,
 3832                                               visitor);
 3833  
 3834                          self.resolve_type(&argument.ty, visitor);
 3835  
 3836                          debug!("(resolving function) recorded argument");
 3837                      }
 3838  
 3839                      self.resolve_type(&declaration.output, visitor);
 3840                  }
 3841              }
 3842  
 3843              // Resolve the function body.
 3844              self.resolve_block(block, visitor);
 3845  
 3846              debug!("(resolving function) leaving function");
 3847          }
 3848  
 3849          self.label_ribs.pop();
 3850          self.value_ribs.pop();
 3851      }

 3855                                     visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 3856          for type_parameter in type_parameters.iter() {
 3857              for bound in type_parameter.bounds.iter() {
 3858                  self.resolve_type_parameter_bound(type_parameter.id, bound, visitor);

 3899      pub fn resolve_struct(@mut self,
 3900                            id: NodeId,
 3901                            generics: &Generics,
 3902                            fields: &[@struct_field],
 3903                            visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 3904          let mut ident_map: HashMap<ast::Ident,@struct_field> = HashMap::new();
 3905          for &field in fields.iter() {
 3906              match field.node.kind {
 3907                  named_field(ident, _) => {

 3909                          Some(&prev_field) => {
 3910                              let ident_str = self.session.str_of(ident);
 3911                              self.resolve_error(field.span,
 3912                                  fmt!("field `%s` is already declared", ident_str));
 3913                              self.session.span_note(prev_field.span,
 3914                                  "Previously declared here");
 3915                          },
 3916                          None => {
 3917                              ident_map.insert(ident, field);
 3918                          }
 3919                      }
 3920                  }
 3921                  _ => ()
 3922              }
 3923          }
 3924  
 3925          // If applicable, create a rib for the type parameters.
 3926          do self.with_type_parameter_rib(HasTypeParameters
 3927                                          (generics, id, 0,
 3928                                           OpaqueFunctionRibKind)) {
 3929  
 3930              // Resolve the type parameters.
 3931              self.resolve_type_parameters(&generics.ty_params, visitor);
 3932  
 3933              // Resolve fields.
 3934              for field in fields.iter() {
 3935                  self.resolve_type(&field.node.ty, visitor);
 3936              }
 3937          }
 3938      }

 3945                            outer_type_parameter_count: uint,
 3946                            visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {

 3948          let type_parameters =
 3949              HasTypeParameters(method_generics,

 3955            sty_static => { NoSelfBinding }

 3959          self.resolve_function(rib_kind,
 3960                                Some(&method.decl),
 3961                                type_parameters,

 3967      pub fn resolve_implementation(@mut self,

 4055      pub fn resolve_local(@mut self, local: @Local, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 4056          let mutability = if local.is_mutbl {Mutable} else {Immutable};
 4057  
 4058          // Resolve the type.
 4059          self.resolve_type(&local.ty, visitor);
 4060  
 4061          // Resolve the initializer, if necessary.
 4062          match local.init {
 4063              None => {
 4064                  // Nothing to do.
 4065              }
 4066              Some(initializer) => {
 4067                  self.resolve_expr(initializer, visitor);
 4068              }
 4069          }
 4070  
 4071          // Resolve the pattern.
 4072          self.resolve_pattern(local.pat, LocalIrrefutableMode, mutability,
 4073                               None, visitor);
 4074      }
 4075  
 4076      // build a map from pattern identifiers to binding-info's.
 4077      // this is done hygienically. This could arise for a macro
 4078      // that expands into an or-pattern where one 'x' was from the
 4079      // user and one 'x' came from the macro.
 4080      pub fn binding_mode_map(@mut self, pat: @Pat) -> BindingMap {
 4081          let mut result = HashMap::new();
 4082          do pat_bindings(self.def_map, pat) |binding_mode, _id, sp, path| {
 4083              let name = mtwt_resolve(path_to_ident(path));
 4084              result.insert(name,
 4085                            binding_info {span: sp,
 4086                                          binding_mode: binding_mode});
 4087          }
 4088          return result;
 4089      }
 4090  
 4091      // check that all of the arms in an or-pattern have exactly the
 4092      // same set of bindings, with the same binding modes for each.
 4093      pub fn check_consistent_bindings(@mut self, arm: &Arm) {
 4094          if arm.pats.len() == 0 { return; }
 4095          let map_0 = self.binding_mode_map(arm.pats[0]);
 4096          for (i, p) in arm.pats.iter().enumerate() {
 4097              let map_i = self.binding_mode_map(*p);
 4098  
 4099              for (&key, &binding_0) in map_0.iter() {
 4100                  match map_i.find(&key) {
 4101                    None => {
 4102                      self.resolve_error(
 4103                          p.span,
 4104                          fmt!("variable `%s` from pattern #1 is \
 4105                                    not bound in pattern #%u",
 4106                               interner_get(key), i + 1));
 4107                    }
 4108                    Some(binding_i) => {
 4109                      if binding_0.binding_mode != binding_i.binding_mode {
 4110                          self.resolve_error(
 4111                              binding_i.span,
 4112                              fmt!("variable `%s` is bound with different \
 4113                                        mode in pattern #%u than in pattern #1",
 4114                                   interner_get(key), i + 1));
 4115                      }
 4116                    }
 4117                  }
 4118              }
 4119  
 4120              for (&key, &binding) in map_i.iter() {
 4121                  if !map_0.contains_key(&key) {
 4122                      self.resolve_error(
 4123                          binding.span,
 4124                          fmt!("variable `%s` from pattern #%u is \
 4125                                    not bound in pattern #1",
 4126                               interner_get(key), i + 1));
 4127                  }
 4128              }
 4129          }
 4130      }
 4131  
 4132      pub fn resolve_arm(@mut self, arm: &Arm, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 4133          self.value_ribs.push(@Rib::new(NormalRibKind));
 4134  
 4135          let bindings_list = @mut HashMap::new();
 4136          for pattern in arm.pats.iter() {
 4137              self.resolve_pattern(*pattern, RefutableMode, Immutable,
 4138                                   Some(bindings_list), visitor);
 4139          }
 4140  
 4141          // This has to happen *after* we determine which
 4142          // pat_idents are variants
 4143          self.check_consistent_bindings(arm);
 4144  
 4145          visit::walk_expr_opt(visitor, arm.guard, ());
 4146          self.resolve_block(&arm.body, visitor);
 4147  
 4148          self.value_ribs.pop();
 4149      }
 4150  
 4151      pub fn resolve_block(@mut self, block: &Block, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 4152          debug!("(resolving block) entering block");
 4153          self.value_ribs.push(@Rib::new(NormalRibKind));
 4154  
 4155          // Move down in the graph, if there's an anonymous module rooted here.
 4156          let orig_module = self.current_module;
 4157          match self.current_module.anonymous_children.find(&block.id) {
 4158              None => { /* Nothing to do. */ }
 4159              Some(&anonymous_module) => {
 4160                  debug!("(resolving block) found anonymous module, moving \
 4161                          down");
 4162                  self.current_module = anonymous_module;
 4163              }
 4164          }
 4165  
 4166          // Descend into the block.
 4167          visit::walk_block(visitor, block, ());
 4168  
 4169          // Move back up.
 4170          self.current_module = orig_module;
 4171  
 4172          self.value_ribs.pop();
 4173          debug!("(resolving block) leaving block");
 4174      }
 4175  
 4176      pub fn resolve_type(@mut self, ty: &Ty, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 4177          match ty.node {
 4178              // Like path expressions, the interpretation of path types depends
 4179              // on whether the path has multiple elements in it or not.
 4180  
 4181              ty_path(ref path, ref bounds, path_id) => {
 4182                  // This is a path in the type namespace. Walk through scopes
 4183                  // scopes looking for it.
 4184                  let mut result_def = None;
 4185  
 4186                  // First, check to see whether the name is a primitive type.
 4187                  if path.segments.len() == 1 {
 4188                      let id = path.segments.last().identifier;
 4189  
 4190                      match self.primitive_type_table
 4191                              .primitive_types
 4192                              .find(&id.name) {
 4193  
 4194                          Some(&primitive_type) => {
 4195                              result_def =
 4196                                  Some(DefPrimTy(primitive_type));
 4197  
 4198                              if path.segments
 4199                                     .iter()
 4200                                     .any(|s| s.lifetime.is_some()) {
 4201                                  self.session.span_err(path.span,
 4202                                                        "lifetime parameters \
 4203                                                         are not allowed on \
 4204                                                         this type")
 4205                              } else if path.segments
 4206                                            .iter()
 4207                                            .any(|s| s.types.len() > 0) {
 4208                                  self.session.span_err(path.span,
 4209                                                        "type parameters are \
 4210                                                         not allowed on this \
 4211                                                         type")
 4212                              }
 4213                          }
 4214                          None => {
 4215                              // Continue.
 4216                          }
 4217                      }
 4218                  }
 4219  
 4220                  match result_def {
 4221                      None => {
 4222                          match self.resolve_path(ty.id,
 4223                                                  path,
 4224                                                  TypeNS,
 4225                                                  true,
 4226                                                  visitor) {
 4227                              Some(def) => {
 4228                                  debug!("(resolving type) resolved `%s` to \
 4229                                          type %?",
 4230                                         self.session.str_of(path.segments
 4231                                                                 .last()
 4232                                                                 .identifier),
 4233                                         def);
 4234                                  result_def = Some(def);
 4235                              }
 4236                              None => {
 4237                                  result_def = None;
 4238                              }
 4239                          }
 4240                      }
 4241                      Some(_) => {}   // Continue.
 4242                  }
 4243  
 4244                  match result_def {
 4245                      Some(def) => {
 4246                          // Write the result into the def map.
 4247                          debug!("(resolving type) writing resolution for `%s` \
 4248                                  (id %d)",
 4249                                 self.path_idents_to_str(path),
 4250                                 path_id);
 4251                          self.record_def(path_id, def);
 4252                      }
 4253                      None => {
 4254                          self.resolve_error
 4255                              (ty.span,
 4256                               fmt!("use of undeclared type name `%s`",
 4257                                    self.path_idents_to_str(path)))
 4258                      }
 4259                  }
 4260  
 4261                  do bounds.map |bound_vec| {
 4262                      for bound in bound_vec.iter() {
 4263                          self.resolve_type_parameter_bound(ty.id, bound, visitor);
 4264                      }
 4265                  };
 4266              }
 4267  
 4268              ty_closure(c) => {
 4269                  do c.bounds.map |bounds| {
 4270                      for bound in bounds.iter() {
 4271                          self.resolve_type_parameter_bound(ty.id, bound, visitor);
 4272                      }
 4273                  };
 4274                  visit::walk_ty(visitor, ty, ());
 4275              }
 4276  
 4277              _ => {
 4278                  // Just resolve embedded types.
 4279                  visit::walk_ty(visitor, ty, ());
 4280              }
 4281          }
 4282      }
 4283  
 4284      pub fn resolve_pattern(@mut self,
 4285                             pattern: @Pat,
 4286                             mode: PatternBindingMode,
 4287                             mutability: Mutability,
 4288                             // Maps idents to the node ID for the (outermost)
 4289                             // pattern that binds them
 4290                             bindings_list: Option<@mut HashMap<Name,NodeId>>,
 4291                             visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 4292          let pat_id = pattern.id;
 4293          do walk_pat(pattern) |pattern| {
 4294              match pattern.node {
 4295                  PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, _)
 4296                          if !path.global && path.segments.len() == 1 => {
 4297  
 4298                      // The meaning of pat_ident with no type parameters
 4299                      // depends on whether an enum variant or unit-like struct
 4300                      // with that name is in scope. The probing lookup has to
 4301                      // be careful not to emit spurious errors. Only matching
 4302                      // patterns (match) can match nullary variants or
 4303                      // unit-like structs. For binding patterns (let), matching
 4304                      // such a value is simply disallowed (since it's rarely
 4305                      // what you want).
 4306  
 4307                      let ident = path.segments[0].identifier;
 4308                      let renamed = mtwt_resolve(ident);
 4309  
 4310                      match self.resolve_bare_identifier_pattern(ident) {
 4311                          FoundStructOrEnumVariant(def)
 4312                                  if mode == RefutableMode => {
 4313                              debug!("(resolving pattern) resolving `%s` to \
 4314                                      struct or enum variant",
 4315                                     interner_get(renamed));
 4316  
 4317                              self.enforce_default_binding_mode(
 4318                                  pattern,
 4319                                  binding_mode,
 4320                                  "an enum variant");
 4321                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4322                          }
 4323                          FoundStructOrEnumVariant(_) => {
 4324                              self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4325                                                    fmt!("declaration of `%s` \
 4326                                                          shadows an enum \
 4327                                                          variant or unit-like \
 4328                                                          struct in scope",
 4329                                                         interner_get(renamed)));
 4330                          }
 4331                          FoundConst(def) if mode == RefutableMode => {
 4332                              debug!("(resolving pattern) resolving `%s` to \
 4333                                      constant",
 4334                                     interner_get(renamed));
 4335  
 4336                              self.enforce_default_binding_mode(
 4337                                  pattern,
 4338                                  binding_mode,
 4339                                  "a constant");
 4340                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4341                          }
 4342                          FoundConst(_) => {
 4343                              self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4344                                                    "only refutable patterns \
 4345                                                     allowed here");
 4346                          }
 4347                          BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved => {
 4348                              debug!("(resolving pattern) binding `%s`",
 4349                                     interner_get(renamed));
 4350  
 4351                              let is_mutable = mutability == Mutable;
 4352  
 4353                              let def = match mode {
 4354                                  RefutableMode => {
 4355                                      // For pattern arms, we must use
 4356                                      // `def_binding` definitions.
 4357  
 4358                                      DefBinding(pattern.id, binding_mode)
 4359                                  }
 4360                                  LocalIrrefutableMode => {
 4361                                      // But for locals, we use `def_local`.
 4362                                      DefLocal(pattern.id, is_mutable)
 4363                                  }
 4364                                  ArgumentIrrefutableMode => {
 4365                                      // And for function arguments, `def_arg`.
 4366                                      DefArg(pattern.id, is_mutable)
 4367                                  }
 4368                              };
 4369  
 4370                              // Record the definition so that later passes
 4371                              // will be able to distinguish variants from
 4372                              // locals in patterns.
 4373  
 4374                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4375  
 4376                              // Add the binding to the local ribs, if it
 4377                              // doesn't already exist in the bindings list. (We
 4378                              // must not add it if it's in the bindings list
 4379                              // because that breaks the assumptions later
 4380                              // passes make about or-patterns.)
 4381  
 4382                              match bindings_list {
 4383                                  Some(bindings_list)
 4384                                  if !bindings_list.contains_key(&renamed) => {
 4385                                      let this = &mut *self;
 4386                                      let last_rib = this.value_ribs[
 4387                                              this.value_ribs.len() - 1];
 4388                                      last_rib.bindings.insert(renamed,
 4389                                                               DlDef(def));
 4390                                      bindings_list.insert(renamed, pat_id);
 4391                                  }
 4392                                  Some(b) => {
 4393                                    if b.find(&renamed) == Some(&pat_id) {
 4394                                        // Then this is a duplicate variable
 4395                                        // in the same disjunct, which is an
 4396                                        // error
 4397                                       self.resolve_error(pattern.span,
 4398                                         fmt!("Identifier `%s` is bound more \
 4399                                               than once in the same pattern",
 4400                                              path_to_str(path, self.session
 4401                                                          .intr())));
 4402                                    }
 4403                                    // Not bound in the same pattern: do nothing
 4404                                  }
 4405                                  None => {
 4406                                      let this = &mut *self;
 4407                                      let last_rib = this.value_ribs[
 4408                                              this.value_ribs.len() - 1];
 4409                                      last_rib.bindings.insert(renamed,
 4410                                                               DlDef(def));
 4411                                  }
 4412                              }
 4413                          }
 4414                      }
 4415  
 4416                      // Check the types in the path pattern.
 4417                      for ty in path.segments
 4418                                    .iter()
 4419                                    .flat_map(|seg| seg.types.iter()) {
 4420                          self.resolve_type(ty, visitor);
 4421                      }
 4422                  }
 4423  
 4424                  PatIdent(binding_mode, ref path, _) => {
 4425                      // This must be an enum variant, struct, or constant.
 4426                      match self.resolve_path(pat_id, path, ValueNS, false, visitor) {
 4427                          Some(def @ DefVariant(*)) |
 4428                                  Some(def @ DefStruct(*)) => {
 4429                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4430                          }
 4431                          Some(def @ DefStatic(*)) => {
 4432                              self.enforce_default_binding_mode(
 4433                                  pattern,
 4434                                  binding_mode,
 4435                                  "a constant");
 4436                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4437                          }
 4438                          Some(_) => {
 4439                              self.resolve_error(
 4440                                  path.span,
 4441                                  fmt!("`%s` is not an enum variant or constant",
 4442                                       self.session.str_of(
 4443                                           path.segments.last().identifier)))
 4444                          }
 4445                          None => {
 4446                              self.resolve_error(path.span,
 4447                                                    "unresolved enum variant");
 4448                          }
 4449                      }
 4450  
 4451                      // Check the types in the path pattern.
 4452                      for ty in path.segments
 4453                                    .iter()
 4454                                    .flat_map(|s| s.types.iter()) {
 4455                          self.resolve_type(ty, visitor);
 4456                      }
 4457                  }
 4458  
 4459                  PatEnum(ref path, _) => {
 4460                      // This must be an enum variant, struct or const.
 4461                      match self.resolve_path(pat_id, path, ValueNS, false, visitor) {
 4462                          Some(def @ DefFn(*))      |
 4463                          Some(def @ DefVariant(*)) |
 4464                          Some(def @ DefStruct(*))  |
 4465                          Some(def @ DefStatic(*)) => {
 4466                              self.record_def(pattern.id, def);
 4467                          }
 4468                          Some(_) => {
 4469                              self.resolve_error(
 4470                                  path.span,
 4471                                  fmt!("`%s` is not an enum variant, struct or const",
 4472                                       self.session
 4473                                           .str_of(path.segments
 4474                                                       .last()
 4475                                                       .identifier)));
 4476                          }
 4477                          None => {
 4478                              self.resolve_error(path.span,
 4479                                                 fmt!("unresolved enum variant, \
 4480                                                      struct or const `%s`",
 4481                                                      self.session
 4482                                                          .str_of(path.segments
 4483                                                                      .last()
 4484                                                                      .identifier)));
 4485                          }
 4486                      }
 4487  
 4488                      // Check the types in the path pattern.
 4489                      for ty in path.segments
 4490                                    .iter()
 4491                                    .flat_map(|s| s.types.iter()) {
 4492                          self.resolve_type(ty, visitor);
 4493                      }
 4494                  }
 4495  
 4496                  PatLit(expr) => {
 4497                      self.resolve_expr(expr, visitor);
 4498                  }
 4499  
 4500                  PatRange(first_expr, last_expr) => {
 4501                      self.resolve_expr(first_expr, visitor);
 4502                      self.resolve_expr(last_expr, visitor);
 4503                  }
 4504  
 4505                  PatStruct(ref path, _, _) => {
 4506                      match self.resolve_path(pat_id, path, TypeNS, false, visitor) {
 4507                          Some(DefTy(class_id))
 4508                                  if self.structs.contains(&class_id) => {
 4509                              let class_def = DefStruct(class_id);
 4510                              self.record_def(pattern.id, class_def);
 4511                          }
 4512                          Some(definition @ DefStruct(class_id)) => {
 4513                              assert!(self.structs.contains(&class_id));
 4514                              self.record_def(pattern.id, definition);
 4515                          }
 4516                          Some(definition @ DefVariant(_, variant_id, _))
 4517                                  if self.structs.contains(&variant_id) => {
 4518                              self.record_def(pattern.id, definition);
 4519                          }
 4520                          result => {
 4521                              debug!("(resolving pattern) didn't find struct \
 4522                                      def: %?", result);
 4523                              self.resolve_error(
 4524                                  path.span,
 4525                                  fmt!("`%s` does not name a structure",
 4526                                       self.path_idents_to_str(path)));
 4527                          }
 4528                      }
 4529                  }
 4530  
 4531                  _ => {
 4532                      // Nothing to do.
 4533                  }
 4534              }
 4535              true
 4536          };
 4537      }

 4539      pub fn resolve_bare_identifier_pattern(@mut self, name: Ident)
 4540                                             ->
 4541                                             BareIdentifierPatternResolution {
 4542          match self.resolve_item_in_lexical_scope(self.current_module,
 4543                                                   name,
 4544                                                   ValueNS,
 4545                                                   SearchThroughModules) {
 4546              Success(target) => {
 4547                  match target.bindings.value_def {
 4548                      None => {
 4549                          fail!("resolved name in the value namespace to a \
 4550                                set of name bindings with no def?!");
 4551                      }
 4552                      Some(def) => {
 4553                          match def.def {
 4554                              def @ DefVariant(*) | def @ DefStruct(*) => {
 4555                                  return FoundStructOrEnumVariant(def);
 4556                              }
 4557                              def @ DefStatic(_, false) => {
 4558                                  return FoundConst(def);
 4559                              }
 4560                              _ => {
 4561                                  return BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved;
 4562                              }
 4563                          }
 4564                      }
 4565                  }
 4566              }
 4567  
 4568              Indeterminate => {
 4569                  fail!("unexpected indeterminate result");
 4570              }
 4571  
 4572              Failed => {
 4573                  return BareIdentifierPatternUnresolved;
 4574              }
 4575          }
 4576      }
 4577  
 4578      /// If `check_ribs` is true, checks the local definitions first; i.e.
 4579      /// doesn't skip straight to the containing module.
 4580      pub fn resolve_path(@mut self,
 4581                          id: NodeId,
 4582                          path: &Path,
 4583                          namespace: Namespace,
 4584                          check_ribs: bool,
 4585                          visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor)
 4586                          -> Option<Def> {
 4587          // First, resolve the types.
 4588          for ty in path.segments.iter().flat_map(|s| s.types.iter()) {
 4589              self.resolve_type(ty, visitor);
 4590          }
 4591  
 4592          if path.global {
 4593              return self.resolve_crate_relative_path(path,
 4594                                                      self.xray_context,
 4595                                                      namespace);
 4596          }
 4597  
 4598          let unqualified_def = self.resolve_identifier(path.segments
 4599                                                            .last()
 4600                                                            .identifier,
 4601                                                        namespace,
 4602                                                        check_ribs,
 4603                                                        path.span);
 4604  
 4605          if path.segments.len() > 1 {
 4606              let def = self.resolve_module_relative_path(path,
 4607                                                          self.xray_context,
 4608                                                          namespace);
 4609              match (def, unqualified_def) {
 4610                  (Some(d), Some(ud)) if d == ud => {
 4611                      self.session.add_lint(unnecessary_qualification,
 4612                                            id,
 4613                                            path.span,
 4614                                            ~"unnecessary qualification");
 4615                  }
 4616                  _ => ()
 4617              }
 4618  
 4619              return def;
 4620          }
 4621  
 4622          return unqualified_def;
 4623      }
 4624  
 4625      // resolve a single identifier (used as a varref)
 4626      pub fn resolve_identifier(@mut self,
 4627                                identifier: Ident,
 4628                                namespace: Namespace,
 4629                                check_ribs: bool,
 4630                                span: Span)
 4631                                -> Option<Def> {
 4632          if check_ribs {
 4633              match self.resolve_identifier_in_local_ribs(identifier,
 4634                                                        namespace,
 4635                                                        span) {
 4636                  Some(def) => {
 4637                      return Some(def);
 4638                  }
 4639                  None => {
 4640                      // Continue.
 4641                  }
 4642              }
 4643          }
 4644  
 4645          return self.resolve_item_by_identifier_in_lexical_scope(identifier,
 4646                                                                  namespace);
 4647      }
 4648  
 4649      // FIXME #4952: Merge me with resolve_name_in_module?
 4650      pub fn resolve_definition_of_name_in_module(@mut self,
 4651                                                  containing_module: @mut Module,
 4652                                                  name: Ident,
 4653                                                  namespace: Namespace,
 4654                                                  xray: XrayFlag)
 4655                                                  -> NameDefinition {
 4656          // First, search children.
 4657          self.populate_module_if_necessary(containing_module);
 4658          match containing_module.children.find(&name.name) {
 4659              Some(child_name_bindings) => {
 4660                  match (child_name_bindings.def_for_namespace(namespace),
 4661                         child_name_bindings.privacy_for_namespace(namespace)) {
 4662                      (Some(def), Some(Public)) => {
 4663                          // Found it. Stop the search here.
 4664                          return ChildNameDefinition(def);
 4665                      }
 4666                      (Some(def), _) if xray == Xray => {
 4667                          // Found it. Stop the search here.
 4668                          return ChildNameDefinition(def);
 4669                      }
 4670                      (Some(_), _) | (None, _) => {
 4671                          // Continue.
 4672                      }
 4673                  }
 4674              }
 4675              None => {
 4676                  // Continue.
 4677              }
 4678          }
 4679  
 4680          // Next, search import resolutions.
 4681          match containing_module.import_resolutions.find(&name.name) {
 4682              Some(import_resolution) if import_resolution.privacy == Public ||
 4683                                         xray == Xray => {
 4684                  match (*import_resolution).target_for_namespace(namespace) {
 4685                      Some(target) => {
 4686                          match (target.bindings.def_for_namespace(namespace),
 4687                                 target.bindings.privacy_for_namespace(
 4688                                      namespace)) {
 4689                              (Some(def), Some(Public)) => {
 4690                                  // Found it.
 4691                                  let id = import_resolution.id(namespace);
 4692                                  self.used_imports.insert(id);
 4693                                  return ImportNameDefinition(def);
 4694                              }
 4695                              (Some(_), _) | (None, _) => {
 4696                                  // This can happen with external impls, due to
 4697                                  // the imperfect way we read the metadata.
 4698                              }
 4699                          }
 4700                      }
 4701                      None => {}
 4702                  }
 4703              }
 4704              Some(_) | None => {}    // Continue.
 4705          }
 4706  
 4707          // Finally, search through external children.
 4708          if namespace == TypeNS {
 4709              match containing_module.external_module_children.find(&name.name) {
 4710                  None => {}
 4711                  Some(module) => {
 4712                      match module.def_id {
 4713                          None => {} // Continue.
 4714                          Some(def_id) => {
 4715                              return ChildNameDefinition(DefMod(def_id));
 4716                          }
 4717                      }
 4718                  }
 4719              }
 4720          }
 4721  
 4722          return NoNameDefinition;
 4723      }

 4725      // resolve a "module-relative" path, e.g. a::b::c
 4726      pub fn resolve_module_relative_path(@mut self,
 4727                                          path: &Path,
 4728                                          xray: XrayFlag,
 4729                                          namespace: Namespace)
 4730                                          -> Option<Def> {
 4731          let module_path_idents = path.segments.init().map(|ps| ps.identifier);
 4732  
 4733          let containing_module;
 4734          match self.resolve_module_path(self.current_module,
 4735                                         module_path_idents,
 4736                                         UseLexicalScope,
 4737                                         path.span,
 4738                                         PathPublicOnlySearch) {
 4739              Failed => {
 4740                  self.resolve_error(path.span,
 4741                                        fmt!("use of undeclared module `%s`",
 4742                                             self.idents_to_str(
 4743                                                 module_path_idents)));
 4744                  return None;
 4745              }
 4746  
 4747              Indeterminate => {
 4748                  fail!("indeterminate unexpected");
 4749              }
 4750  
 4751              Success(resulting_module) => {
 4752                  containing_module = resulting_module;
 4753              }
 4754          }
 4755  
 4756          let ident = path.segments.last().identifier;
 4757          let def = match self.resolve_definition_of_name_in_module(containing_module,
 4758                                                          ident,
 4759                                                          namespace,
 4760                                                          xray) {
 4761              NoNameDefinition => {
 4762                  // We failed to resolve the name. Report an error.
 4763                  return None;
 4764              }
 4765              ChildNameDefinition(def) | ImportNameDefinition(def) => {
 4766                  def
 4767              }
 4768          };
 4769          match containing_module.kind {
 4770              TraitModuleKind | ImplModuleKind => {
 4771                  match self.method_map.find(&ident.name) {
 4772                      Some(s) => {
 4773                          match containing_module.def_id {
 4774                              Some(def_id) if s.contains(&def_id) => {
 4775                                  debug!("containing module was a trait or impl \
 4776                                          and name was a method -> not resolved");
 4777                                  return None;
 4778                              },
 4779                              _ => (),
 4780                          }
 4781                      },
 4782                      None => (),
 4783                  }
 4784              },
 4785              _ => (),
 4786          };
 4787          return Some(def);
 4788      }

 4953      pub fn find_best_match_for_name(@mut self,
 4954                                      name: &str,
 4955                                      max_distance: uint)
 4956                                      -> Option<@str> {
 4957          let this = &mut *self;
 4958  
 4959          let mut maybes: ~[@str] = ~[];
 4960          let mut values: ~[uint] = ~[];
 4961  
 4962          let mut j = this.value_ribs.len();
 4963          while j != 0 {
 4964              j -= 1;
 4965              for (&k, _) in this.value_ribs[j].bindings.iter() {
 4966                  maybes.push(interner_get(k));
 4967                  values.push(uint::max_value);
 4968              }
 4969          }
 4970  
 4971          let mut smallest = 0;
 4972          for (i, &other) in maybes.iter().enumerate() {
 4973              values[i] = name.lev_distance(other);
 4974  
 4975              if values[i] <= values[smallest] {
 4976                  smallest = i;
 4977              }
 4978          }
 4979  
 4980          if values.len() > 0 &&
 4981              values[smallest] != uint::max_value &&
 4982              values[smallest] < name.len() + 2 &&
 4983              values[smallest] <= max_distance &&
 4984              name != maybes[smallest] {
 4985  
 4986              Some(maybes.swap_remove(smallest))
 4987  
 4988          } else {
 4989              None
 4990          }
 4991      }

 4993      pub fn name_exists_in_scope_struct(@mut self, name: &str) -> bool {
 4994          let this = &mut *self;
 4995  
 4996          let mut i = this.type_ribs.len();
 4997          while i != 0 {
 4998            i -= 1;
 4999            match this.type_ribs[i].kind {
 5000              MethodRibKind(node_id, _) =>
 5001                for item in this.crate.module.items.iter() {
 5002                  if item.id == node_id {
 5003                    match item.node {
 5004                      item_struct(class_def, _) => {
 5005                        for field in class_def.fields.iter() {
 5006                          match field.node.kind {
 5007                            unnamed_field => {},
 5008                            named_field(ident, _) => {
 5009                                if str::eq_slice(this.session.str_of(ident),
 5010                                                 name) {
 5011                                  return true
 5012                                }
 5013                              }
 5014                          }
 5015                        }
 5016                      }
 5017                      _ => {}
 5018                    }
 5019                  }
 5020              },
 5021            _ => {}
 5022          }
 5023        }
 5024        return false;
 5025      }

 5027      pub fn resolve_expr(@mut self, expr: @Expr, visitor: &mut ResolveVisitor) {
 5028          // First, record candidate traits for this expression if it could
 5029          // result in the invocation of a method call.
 5030  
 5031          self.record_candidate_traits_for_expr_if_necessary(expr);
 5032  
 5033          // Next, resolve the node.
 5034          match expr.node {
 5035              // The interpretation of paths depends on whether the path has
 5036              // multiple elements in it or not.
 5037  
 5038              ExprPath(ref path) => {
 5039                  // This is a local path in the value namespace. Walk through
 5040                  // scopes looking for it.
 5041  
 5042                  match self.resolve_path(expr.id, path, ValueNS, true, visitor) {
 5043                      Some(def) => {
 5044                          // Write the result into the def map.
 5045                          debug!("(resolving expr) resolved `%s`",
 5046                                 self.path_idents_to_str(path));
 5047  
 5048                          // First-class methods are not supported yet; error
 5049                          // out here.
 5050                          match def {
 5051                              DefMethod(*) => {
 5052                                  self.resolve_error(expr.span,
 5053                                                        "first-class methods \
 5054                                                         are not supported");
 5055                                  self.session.span_note(expr.span,
 5056                                                         "call the method \
 5057                                                          using the `.` \
 5058                                                          syntax");
 5059                              }
 5060                              _ => {}
 5061                          }
 5062  
 5063                          self.record_def(expr.id, def);
 5064                      }
 5065                      None => {
 5066                          let wrong_name = self.path_idents_to_str(path);
 5067                          if self.name_exists_in_scope_struct(wrong_name) {
 5068                              self.resolve_error(expr.span,
 5069                                          fmt!("unresolved name `%s`. \
 5070                                              Did you mean `self.%s`?",
 5071                                          wrong_name,
 5072                                          wrong_name));
 5073                          }
 5074                          else {
 5075                              // Be helpful if the name refers to a struct
 5076                              // (The pattern matching def_tys where the id is in self.structs
 5077                              // matches on regular structs while excluding tuple- and enum-like
 5078                              // structs, which wouldn't result in this error.)
 5079                              match self.with_no_errors(||
 5080                                  self.resolve_path(expr.id, path, TypeNS, false, visitor)) {
 5081                                  Some(DefTy(struct_id))
 5082                                    if self.structs.contains(&struct_id) => {
 5083                                      self.resolve_error(expr.span,
 5084                                              fmt!("`%s` is a structure name, but this expression \
 5085                                                  uses it like a function name", wrong_name));
 5086  
 5087                                      self.session.span_note(expr.span, fmt!("Did you mean to write: \
 5088                                                  `%s { /* fields */ }`?", wrong_name));
 5089  
 5090                                  }
 5091                                  _ =>
 5092                                     // limit search to 5 to reduce the number
 5093                                     // of stupid suggestions
 5094                                     match self.find_best_match_for_name(wrong_name, 5) {
 5095                                         Some(m) => {
 5096                                             self.resolve_error(expr.span,
 5097                                                 fmt!("unresolved name `%s`. \
 5098                                                     Did you mean `%s`?",
 5099                                                     wrong_name, m));
 5100                                         }
 5101                                         None => {
 5102                                             self.resolve_error(expr.span,
 5103                                                  fmt!("unresolved name `%s`.",
 5104                                                      wrong_name));
 5105                                         }
 5106                                     }
 5107                              }
 5108                          }
 5109                      }
 5110                  }
 5111  
 5112                  visit::walk_expr(visitor, expr, ());
 5113              }
 5114  
 5115              ExprFnBlock(ref fn_decl, ref block) => {
 5116                  self.resolve_function(FunctionRibKind(expr.id, block.id),
 5117                                        Some(fn_decl),
 5118                                        NoTypeParameters,
 5119                                        block,
 5120                                        NoSelfBinding,
 5121                                        visitor);
 5122              }
 5123  
 5124              ExprStruct(ref path, _, _) => {
 5125                  // Resolve the path to the structure it goes to.
 5126                  match self.resolve_path(expr.id, path, TypeNS, false, visitor) {
 5127                      Some(DefTy(class_id)) | Some(DefStruct(class_id))
 5128                              if self.structs.contains(&class_id) => {
 5129                          let class_def = DefStruct(class_id);
 5130                          self.record_def(expr.id, class_def);
 5131                      }
 5132                      Some(definition @ DefVariant(_, class_id, _))
 5133                              if self.structs.contains(&class_id) => {
 5134                          self.record_def(expr.id, definition);
 5135                      }
 5136                      result => {
 5137                          debug!("(resolving expression) didn't find struct \
 5138                                  def: %?", result);
 5139                          self.resolve_error(
 5140                              path.span,
 5141                              fmt!("`%s` does not name a structure",
 5142                                   self.path_idents_to_str(path)));
 5143                      }
 5144                  }
 5145  
 5146                  visit::walk_expr(visitor, expr, ());
 5147              }
 5148  
 5149              ExprLoop(_, Some(label)) => {
 5150                  do self.with_label_rib {
 5151                      {
 5152                          let this = &mut *self;
 5153                          let def_like = DlDef(DefLabel(expr.id));
 5154                          let rib = this.label_ribs[this.label_ribs.len() - 1];
 5155                          // plain insert (no renaming)
 5156                          rib.bindings.insert(label.name, def_like);
 5157                      }
 5158  
 5159                      visit::walk_expr(visitor, expr, ());
 5160                  }
 5161              }
 5162  
 5163              ExprForLoop(*) => fail!("non-desugared expr_for_loop"),
 5164  
 5165              ExprBreak(Some(label)) | ExprAgain(Some(label)) => {
 5166                  match self.search_ribs(self.label_ribs, label, expr.span,
 5167                                         DontAllowCapturingSelf) {

 5286      pub fn search_for_traits_containing_method(@mut self, name: Ident)
 5287                                                 -> ~[DefId] {
 5288          debug!("(searching for traits containing method) looking for '%s'",
 5289                 self.session.str_of(name));
 5290  
 5291          let mut found_traits = ~[];
 5292          let mut search_module = self.current_module;
 5293          match self.method_map.find(&name.name) {
 5294              Some(candidate_traits) => loop {
 5295                  // Look for the current trait.
 5296                  match self.current_trait_refs {
 5297                      Some(ref trait_def_ids) => {
 5298                          for trait_def_id in trait_def_ids.iter() {
 5299                              if candidate_traits.contains(trait_def_id) {
 5300                                  self.add_trait_info(&mut found_traits,
 5301                                                      *trait_def_id,
 5302                                                      name);
 5303                              }
 5304                          }
 5305                      }
 5306                      None => {
 5307                          // Nothing to do.
 5308                      }
 5309                  }
 5310  
 5311                  // Look for trait children.
 5312                  self.populate_module_if_necessary(search_module);
 5313                  for (_, &child_name_bindings) in
 5314                          search_module.children.iter() {
 5315                      match child_name_bindings.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 5316                          Some(def) => {
 5317                              match def {
 5318                                  DefTrait(trait_def_id) => {
 5319                                      if candidate_traits.contains(&trait_def_id) {
 5320                                          self.add_trait_info(
 5321                                              &mut found_traits,
 5322                                              trait_def_id, name);
 5323                                      }
 5324                                  }
 5325                                  _ => {
 5326                                      // Continue.
 5327                                  }
 5328                              }
 5329                          }
 5330                          None => {
 5331                              // Continue.
 5332                          }
 5333                      }
 5334                  }
 5335  
 5336                  // Look for imports.
 5337                  for (_, &import_resolution) in search_module.import_resolutions.iter() {
 5338                      match import_resolution.target_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 5339                          None => {
 5340                              // Continue.
 5341                          }
 5342                          Some(target) => {
 5343                              match target.bindings.def_for_namespace(TypeNS) {
 5344                                  Some(def) => {
 5345                                      match def {
 5346                                          DefTrait(trait_def_id) => {
 5347                                              if candidate_traits.contains(&trait_def_id) {
 5348                                                  self.add_trait_info(
 5349                                                      &mut found_traits,
 5350                                                      trait_def_id, name);
 5351                                                  self.used_imports.insert(
 5352                                                      import_resolution.type_id);
 5353                                              }
 5354                                          }
 5355                                          _ => {
 5356                                              // Continue.
 5357                                          }
 5358                                      }
 5359                                  }
 5360                                  None => {
 5361                                      // Continue.
 5362                                  }
 5363                              }
 5364                          }
 5365                      }
 5366                  }
 5367  
 5368                  // Move to the next parent.
 5369                  match search_module.parent_link {
 5370                      NoParentLink => {
 5371                          // Done.
 5372                          break;
 5373                      }
 5374                      ModuleParentLink(parent_module, _) |
 5375                      BlockParentLink(parent_module, _) => {
 5376                          search_module = parent_module;
 5377                      }
 5378                  }
 5379              },
 5380              _ => ()
 5381          }
 5382  
 5383          return found_traits;
 5384      }
